71#define LLVM_READOBJ_ENUM_CASE(ns, enum) \
72 case ns::enum: \
73 return #enum;
74
75#define ENUM_ENT(enum, altName) \
76 { #enum, altName, ELF::enum }
77
78#define ENUM_ENT_1(enum) \
79 { #enum, #enum, ELF::enum }
80
81#define LLVM_READOBJ_PHDR_ENUM(ns, enum) \
82 case ns::enum: \
83 return std::string(#enum).substr(3);

118/// Represents a contiguous uniform range in the file. We cannot just create a
119/// range directly because when creating one of these from the .dynamic table
120/// the size, entity size and virtual address are different entries in arbitrary
121/// order (DT_REL, DT_RELSZ, DT_RELENT for example).
122struct DynRegionInfo {
123 DynRegionInfo() = default;
124 DynRegionInfo(const void *A, uint64_t S, uint64_t ES)
125 : Addr(A), Size(S), EntSize(ES) {}
126
127 /// Address in current address space.
128 const void *Addr = nullptr;
129 /// Size in bytes of the region.
130 uint64_t Size = 0;
131 /// Size of each entity in the region.
132 uint64_t EntSize = 0;
133
134 template <typename Type> ArrayRef<Type> getAsArrayRef() const {
135 const Type *Start = reinterpret_cast<const Type *>(Addr);
136 if (!Start)
137 return {Start, Start};
138 if (EntSize != sizeof(Type) || Size % EntSize)
139 reportError("Invalid entity size");
140 return {Start, Start + (Size / EntSize)};
141 }
142};

191 DynRegionInfo checkDRI(DynRegionInfo DRI) {
192 const ELFFile<ELFT> *Obj = ObjF->getELFFile();
193 if (DRI.Addr < Obj->base() ||
194 reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t *>(DRI.Addr) + DRI.Size >
195 Obj->base() + Obj->getBufSize())
196 error(llvm::object::object_error::parse_failed);
197 return DRI;
198 }
199
200 DynRegionInfo createDRIFrom(const Elf_Phdr *P, uintX_t EntSize) {
201 return checkDRI(
202 {ObjF->getELFFile()->base() + P->p_offset, P->p_filesz, EntSize});
203 }
204
205 DynRegionInfo createDRIFrom(const Elf_Shdr *S) {
206 return checkDRI(
207 {ObjF->getELFFile()->base() + S->sh_offset, S->sh_size, S->sh_entsize});
208 }

241 // Records for each version index the corresponding Verdef or Vernaux entry.
242 // This is filled the first time LoadVersionMap() is called.
243 class VersionMapEntry : public PointerIntPair<const void *, 1> {
244 public:
245 // If the integer is 0, this is an Elf_Verdef*.
246 // If the integer is 1, this is an Elf_Vernaux*.
247 VersionMapEntry() : PointerIntPair<const void *, 1>(nullptr, 0) {}
248 VersionMapEntry(const Elf_Verdef *verdef)
249 : PointerIntPair<const void *, 1>(verdef, 0) {}
250 VersionMapEntry(const Elf_Vernaux *vernaux)
251 : PointerIntPair<const void *, 1>(vernaux, 1) {}
252
253 bool isNull() const { return getPointer() == nullptr; }
254 bool isVerdef() const { return !isNull() && getInt() == 0; }
255 bool isVernaux() const { return !isNull() && getInt() == 1; }
256 const Elf_Verdef *getVerdef() const {
257 return isVerdef() ? (const Elf_Verdef *)getPointer() : nullptr;
258 }
259 const Elf_Vernaux *getVernaux() const {
260 return isVernaux() ? (const Elf_Vernaux *)getPointer() : nullptr;
261 }
262 };
263 mutable SmallVector<VersionMapEntry, 16> VersionMap;
264
265public:
266 Elf_Dyn_Range dynamic_table() const {
267 // A valid .dynamic section contains an array of entries terminated
268 // with a DT_NULL entry. However, sometimes the section content may
269 // continue past the DT_NULL entry, so to dump the section correctly,
270 // we first find the end of the entries by iterating over them.
271 Elf_Dyn_Range Table = DynamicTable.getAsArrayRef<Elf_Dyn>();
272
273 size_t Size = 0;
274 while (Size < Table.size())
275 if (Table[Size++].getTag() == DT_NULL)
276 break;
277
278 return Table.slice(0, Size);
279 }
280
281 Elf_Sym_Range dynamic_symbols() const {
282 return DynSymRegion.getAsArrayRef<Elf_Sym>();
283 }
284
285 Elf_Rel_Range dyn_rels() const;
286 Elf_Rela_Range dyn_relas() const;
287 Elf_Relr_Range dyn_relrs() const;
288 std::string getFullSymbolName(const Elf_Sym *Symbol, StringRef StrTable,
289 bool IsDynamic) const;
290 void getSectionNameIndex(const Elf_Sym *Symbol, const Elf_Sym *FirstSym,
291 StringRef &SectionName,
292 unsigned &SectionIndex) const;
293 std::string getStaticSymbolName(uint32_t Index) const;
294 StringRef getSymbolVersionByIndex(StringRef StrTab,
295 uint32_t VersionSymbolIndex,
296 bool &IsDefault) const;
297
298 void printSymbolsHelper(bool IsDynamic) const;
299 void printDynamicEntry(raw_ostream &OS, uint64_t Type, uint64_t Value) const;
300
301 const Elf_Shdr *getDotSymtabSec() const { return DotSymtabSec; }
302 const Elf_Shdr *getDotCGProfileSec() const { return DotCGProfileSec; }
303 const Elf_Shdr *getDotAddrsigSec() const { return DotAddrsigSec; }
304 ArrayRef<Elf_Word> getShndxTable() const { return ShndxTable; }
305 StringRef getDynamicStringTable() const { return DynamicStringTable; }
306 const DynRegionInfo &getDynRelRegion() const { return DynRelRegion; }
307 const DynRegionInfo &getDynRelaRegion() const { return DynRelaRegion; }
308 const DynRegionInfo &getDynRelrRegion() const { return DynRelrRegion; }
309 const DynRegionInfo &getDynPLTRelRegion() const { return DynPLTRelRegion; }
310 const DynRegionInfo &getDynamicTableRegion() const { return DynamicTable; }
311 const Elf_Hash *getHashTable() const { return HashTable; }
312 const Elf_GnuHash *getGnuHashTable() const { return GnuHashTable; }
313};

315template <class ELFT>
316void ELFDumper<ELFT>::printSymbolsHelper(bool IsDynamic) const {
317 StringRef StrTable, SymtabName;
318 size_t Entries = 0;
319 Elf_Sym_Range Syms(nullptr, nullptr);
320 const ELFFile<ELFT> *Obj = ObjF->getELFFile();
321 if (IsDynamic) {
322 StrTable = DynamicStringTable;
323 Syms = dynamic_symbols();
324 SymtabName = DynSymtabName;
325 if (DynSymRegion.Addr)
326 Entries = DynSymRegion.Size / DynSymRegion.EntSize;
327 } else {
328 if (!DotSymtabSec)
329 return;
330 StrTable = unwrapOrError(Obj->getStringTableForSymtab(*DotSymtabSec));
331 Syms = unwrapOrError(Obj->symbols(DotSymtabSec));
332 SymtabName = unwrapOrError(Obj->getSectionName(DotSymtabSec));
333 Entries = DotSymtabSec->getEntityCount();
334 }
335 if (Syms.begin() == Syms.end())
336 return;
337 ELFDumperStyle->printSymtabMessage(Obj, SymtabName, Entries);
338 for (const auto &Sym : Syms)
339 ELFDumperStyle->printSymbol(Obj, &Sym, Syms.begin(), StrTable, IsDynamic);
340}

435
436 template <typename T, typename TEnum>
437 std::string printEnum(T Value, ArrayRef<EnumEntry<TEnum>> EnumValues) {
438 for (const auto &EnumItem : EnumValues)
439 if (EnumItem.Value == Value)
440 return EnumItem.AltName;
441 return to_hexString(Value, false);
442 }
443
444 template <typename T, typename TEnum>
445 std::string printFlags(T Value, ArrayRef<EnumEntry<TEnum>> EnumValues,
446 TEnum EnumMask1 = {}, TEnum EnumMask2 = {},
447 TEnum EnumMask3 = {}) {
448 std::string Str;
449 for (const auto &Flag : EnumValues) {
450 if (Flag.Value == 0)
451 continue;
452
453 TEnum EnumMask{};
454 if (Flag.Value & EnumMask1)
455 EnumMask = EnumMask1;
456 else if (Flag.Value & EnumMask2)
457 EnumMask = EnumMask2;
458 else if (Flag.Value & EnumMask3)
459 EnumMask = EnumMask3;
460 bool IsEnum = (Flag.Value & EnumMask) != 0;
461 if ((!IsEnum && (Value & Flag.Value) == Flag.Value) ||
462 (IsEnum && (Value & EnumMask) == Flag.Value)) {
463 if (!Str.empty())
464 Str += ", ";
465 Str += Flag.AltName;
466 }
467 }
468 return Str;
469 }
470
471 formatted_raw_ostream &printField(struct Field F) {
472 if (F.Column != 0)
473 OS.PadToColumn(F.Column);
474 OS << F.Str;
475 OS.flush();
476 return OS;
477 }
478 void printHashedSymbol(const ELFO *Obj, const Elf_Sym *FirstSym, uint32_t Sym,
479 StringRef StrTable, uint32_t Bucket);
480 void printRelocHeader(unsigned SType);
481 void printRelocation(const ELFO *Obj, const Elf_Shdr *SymTab,
482 const Elf_Rela &R, bool IsRela);
483 void printRelocation(const ELFO *Obj, const Elf_Sym *Sym,
484 StringRef SymbolName, const Elf_Rela &R, bool IsRela);

487 std::string getSymbolSectionNdx(const ELFO *Obj, const Elf_Sym *Symbol,

490 bool checkTLSSections(const Elf_Phdr &Phdr, const Elf_Shdr &Sec);

546namespace llvm {
547
548template <class ELFT>
549static std::error_code createELFDumper(const ELFObjectFile<ELFT> *Obj,
550 ScopedPrinter &Writer,
551 std::unique_ptr<ObjDumper> &Result) {
552 Result.reset(new ELFDumper<ELFT>(Obj, Writer));
553 return readobj_error::success;
554}
555
556std::error_code createELFDumper(const object::ObjectFile *Obj,
557 ScopedPrinter &Writer,
558 std::unique_ptr<ObjDumper> &Result) {
559 // Little-endian 32-bit
560 if (const ELF32LEObjectFile *ELFObj = dyn_cast<ELF32LEObjectFile>(Obj))
561 return createELFDumper(ELFObj, Writer, Result);
562
563 // Big-endian 32-bit
564 if (const ELF32BEObjectFile *ELFObj = dyn_cast<ELF32BEObjectFile>(Obj))
565 return createELFDumper(ELFObj, Writer, Result);
566
567 // Little-endian 64-bit
568 if (const ELF64LEObjectFile *ELFObj = dyn_cast<ELF64LEObjectFile>(Obj))
569 return createELFDumper(ELFObj, Writer, Result);
570
571 // Big-endian 64-bit
572 if (const ELF64BEObjectFile *ELFObj = dyn_cast<ELF64BEObjectFile>(Obj))
573 return createELFDumper(ELFObj, Writer, Result);
574
575 return readobj_error::unsupported_obj_file_format;
576}

580// Iterate through the versions needed section, and place each Elf_Vernaux
581// in the VersionMap according to its index.
582template <class ELFT>
583void ELFDumper<ELFT>::LoadVersionNeeds(const Elf_Shdr *Sec) const {
584 unsigned VerneedSize = Sec->sh_size; // Size of section in bytes
585 unsigned VerneedEntries = Sec->sh_info; // Number of Verneed entries
586 const uint8_t *VerneedStart = reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t *>(
587 ObjF->getELFFile()->base() + Sec->sh_offset);
588 const uint8_t *VerneedEnd = VerneedStart + VerneedSize;
589 // The first Verneed entry is at the start of the section.
590 const uint8_t *VerneedBuf = VerneedStart;
591 for (unsigned VerneedIndex = 0; VerneedIndex < VerneedEntries;
592 ++VerneedIndex) {
593 if (VerneedBuf + sizeof(Elf_Verneed) > VerneedEnd)
594 report_fatal_error("Section ended unexpectedly while scanning "
595 "version needed records.");
596 const Elf_Verneed *Verneed =
597 reinterpret_cast<const Elf_Verneed *>(VerneedBuf);
598 if (Verneed->vn_version != ELF::VER_NEED_CURRENT)
599 report_fatal_error("Unexpected verneed version");
600 // Iterate through the Vernaux entries
601 const uint8_t *VernauxBuf = VerneedBuf + Verneed->vn_aux;
602 for (unsigned VernauxIndex = 0; VernauxIndex < Verneed->vn_cnt;
603 ++VernauxIndex) {
604 if (VernauxBuf + sizeof(Elf_Vernaux) > VerneedEnd)
605 report_fatal_error("Section ended unexpected while scanning auxiliary "
606 "version needed records.");
607 const Elf_Vernaux *Vernaux =
608 reinterpret_cast<const Elf_Vernaux *>(VernauxBuf);
609 size_t Index = Vernaux->vna_other & ELF::VERSYM_VERSION;
610 if (Index >= VersionMap.size())
611 VersionMap.resize(Index + 1);
612 VersionMap[Index] = VersionMapEntry(Vernaux);
613 VernauxBuf += Vernaux->vna_next;
614 }
615 VerneedBuf += Verneed->vn_next;
616 }
617}
618
619// Iterate through the version definitions, and place each Elf_Verdef
620// in the VersionMap according to its index.
621template <class ELFT>
622void ELFDumper<ELFT>::LoadVersionDefs(const Elf_Shdr *Sec) const {
623 unsigned VerdefSize = Sec->sh_size; // Size of section in bytes
624 unsigned VerdefEntries = Sec->sh_info; // Number of Verdef entries
625 const uint8_t *VerdefStart = reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t *>(
626 ObjF->getELFFile()->base() + Sec->sh_offset);
627 const uint8_t *VerdefEnd = VerdefStart + VerdefSize;
628 // The first Verdef entry is at the start of the section.
629 const uint8_t *VerdefBuf = VerdefStart;
630 for (unsigned VerdefIndex = 0; VerdefIndex < VerdefEntries; ++VerdefIndex) {
631 if (VerdefBuf + sizeof(Elf_Verdef) > VerdefEnd)
632 report_fatal_error("Section ended unexpectedly while scanning "
633 "version definitions.");
634 const Elf_Verdef *Verdef = reinterpret_cast<const Elf_Verdef *>(VerdefBuf);
635 if (Verdef->vd_version != ELF::VER_DEF_CURRENT)
636 report_fatal_error("Unexpected verdef version");
637 size_t Index = Verdef->vd_ndx & ELF::VERSYM_VERSION;
638 if (Index >= VersionMap.size())
639 VersionMap.resize(Index + 1);
640 VersionMap[Index] = VersionMapEntry(Verdef);
641 VerdefBuf += Verdef->vd_next;
642 }
643}
644
645template <class ELFT> void ELFDumper<ELFT>::LoadVersionMap() const {
646 // If there is no dynamic symtab or version table, there is nothing to do.
647 if (!DynSymRegion.Addr || !SymbolVersionSection)
648 return;
649
650 // Has the VersionMap already been loaded?
651 if (!VersionMap.empty())
652 return;
653
654 // The first two version indexes are reserved.
655 // Index 0 is LOCAL, index 1 is GLOBAL.
656 VersionMap.push_back(VersionMapEntry());
657 VersionMap.push_back(VersionMapEntry());
658
659 if (SymbolVersionDefSection)
660 LoadVersionDefs(SymbolVersionDefSection);
661
662 if (SymbolVersionNeedSection)
663 LoadVersionNeeds(SymbolVersionNeedSection);
664}
665
666template <typename ELFT>
667StringRef ELFDumper<ELFT>::getSymbolVersion(StringRef StrTab,
668 const Elf_Sym *Sym,
669 bool &IsDefault) const {
670 // This is a dynamic symbol. Look in the GNU symbol version table.
671 if (!SymbolVersionSection) {
672 // No version table.
673 IsDefault = false;
674 return "";
675 }
676
677 // Determine the position in the symbol table of this entry.
678 size_t EntryIndex = (reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(Sym) -
679 reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(DynSymRegion.Addr)) /
680 sizeof(Elf_Sym);
681
682 // Get the corresponding version index entry.
683 const Elf_Versym *Versym =
684 unwrapOrError(ObjF->getELFFile()->template getEntry<Elf_Versym>(
685 SymbolVersionSection, EntryIndex));
686 return this->getSymbolVersionByIndex(StrTab, Versym->vs_index, IsDefault);
687}
688
689static std::string maybeDemangle(StringRef Name) {
690 return opts::Demangle ? demangle(Name) : Name.str();
691}
692
693template <typename ELFT>
694std::string ELFDumper<ELFT>::getStaticSymbolName(uint32_t Index) const {
695 const ELFFile<ELFT> *Obj = ObjF->getELFFile();
696 StringRef StrTable =
697 unwrapOrError(Obj->getStringTableForSymtab(*DotSymtabSec));
698 Elf_Sym_Range Syms = unwrapOrError(Obj->symbols(DotSymtabSec));
699 if (Index >= Syms.size())
700 reportError("Invalid symbol index");
701 const Elf_Sym *Sym = &Syms[Index];
702 return maybeDemangle(unwrapOrError(Sym->getName(StrTable)));
703}
704
705template <typename ELFT>
706StringRef ELFDumper<ELFT>::getSymbolVersionByIndex(StringRef StrTab,
707 uint32_t SymbolVersionIndex,
708 bool &IsDefault) const {
709 size_t VersionIndex = SymbolVersionIndex & VERSYM_VERSION;
710
711 // Special markers for unversioned symbols.
712 if (VersionIndex == VER_NDX_LOCAL || VersionIndex == VER_NDX_GLOBAL) {
713 IsDefault = false;
714 return "";
715 }
716
717 // Lookup this symbol in the version table.
718 LoadVersionMap();
719 if (VersionIndex >= VersionMap.size() || VersionMap[VersionIndex].isNull())
720 reportError("Invalid version entry");
721 const VersionMapEntry &Entry = VersionMap[VersionIndex];
722
723 // Get the version name string.
724 size_t NameOffset;
725 if (Entry.isVerdef()) {
726 // The first Verdaux entry holds the name.
727 NameOffset = Entry.getVerdef()->getAux()->vda_name;
728 IsDefault = !(SymbolVersionIndex & VERSYM_HIDDEN);
729 } else {
730 NameOffset = Entry.getVernaux()->vna_name;
731 IsDefault = false;
732 }
733 if (NameOffset >= StrTab.size())
734 reportError("Invalid string offset");
735 return StrTab.data() + NameOffset;
736}
737
738template <typename ELFT>
739std::string ELFDumper<ELFT>::getFullSymbolName(const Elf_Sym *Symbol,
740 StringRef StrTable,
741 bool IsDynamic) const {
742 std::string SymbolName =
743 maybeDemangle(unwrapOrError(Symbol->getName(StrTable)));
744
745 if (SymbolName.empty() && Symbol->getType() == ELF::STT_SECTION) {
746 unsigned SectionIndex;
747 StringRef SectionName;
748 Elf_Sym_Range Syms =
749 unwrapOrError(ObjF->getELFFile()->symbols(DotSymtabSec));
750 getSectionNameIndex(Symbol, Syms.begin(), SectionName, SectionIndex);
751 return SectionName;
752 }
753
754 if (!IsDynamic)
755 return SymbolName;
756
757 bool IsDefault;
758 StringRef Version = getSymbolVersion(StrTable, &*Symbol, IsDefault);
759 if (!Version.empty()) {
760 SymbolName += (IsDefault ? "@@" : "@");
761 SymbolName += Version;
762 }
763 return SymbolName;
764}
765
766template <typename ELFT>
767void ELFDumper<ELFT>::getSectionNameIndex(const Elf_Sym *Symbol,
768 const Elf_Sym *FirstSym,
769 StringRef &SectionName,
770 unsigned &SectionIndex) const {
771 SectionIndex = Symbol->st_shndx;
772 if (Symbol->isUndefined())
773 SectionName = "Undefined";
774 else if (Symbol->isProcessorSpecific())
775 SectionName = "Processor Specific";
776 else if (Symbol->isOSSpecific())
777 SectionName = "Operating System Specific";
778 else if (Symbol->isAbsolute())
779 SectionName = "Absolute";
780 else if (Symbol->isCommon())
781 SectionName = "Common";
782 else if (Symbol->isReserved() && SectionIndex != SHN_XINDEX)
783 SectionName = "Reserved";
784 else {
785 if (SectionIndex == SHN_XINDEX)
786 SectionIndex = unwrapOrError(object::getExtendedSymbolTableIndex<ELFT>(
787 Symbol, FirstSym, ShndxTable));
788 const ELFFile<ELFT> *Obj = ObjF->getELFFile();
789 const typename ELFT::Shdr *Sec =
790 unwrapOrError(Obj->getSection(SectionIndex));
791 SectionName = unwrapOrError(Obj->getSectionName(Sec));
792 }
793}
794
795template <class ELFO>
796static const typename ELFO::Elf_Shdr *
797findNotEmptySectionByAddress(const ELFO *Obj, uint64_t Addr) {
798 for (const auto &Shdr : unwrapOrError(Obj->sections()))
799 if (Shdr.sh_addr == Addr && Shdr.sh_size > 0)
800 return &Shdr;
801 return nullptr;
802}
803
804template <class ELFO>
805static const typename ELFO::Elf_Shdr *findSectionByName(const ELFO &Obj,
806 StringRef Name) {
807 for (const auto &Shdr : unwrapOrError(Obj.sections())) {
808 if (Name == unwrapOrError(Obj.getSectionName(&Shdr)))
809 return &Shdr;
810 }
811 return nullptr;
812}

1105static std::string getGNUFlags(uint64_t Flags) {
1106 std::string Str;
1107 for (auto Entry : ElfSectionFlags) {
1108 uint64_t Flag = Entry.Value & Flags;
1109 Flags &= ~Entry.Value;
1110 switch (Flag) {
1111 case ELF::SHF_WRITE:
1112 case ELF::SHF_ALLOC:
1113 case ELF::SHF_EXECINSTR:
1114 case ELF::SHF_MERGE:
1115 case ELF::SHF_STRINGS:
1116 case ELF::SHF_INFO_LINK:
1117 case ELF::SHF_LINK_ORDER:
1118 case ELF::SHF_OS_NONCONFORMING:
1119 case ELF::SHF_GROUP:
1120 case ELF::SHF_TLS:
1121 case ELF::SHF_EXCLUDE:
1122 Str += Entry.AltName;
1123 break;
1124 default:
1125 if (Flag & ELF::SHF_MASKOS)
1126 Str += "o";
1127 else if (Flag & ELF::SHF_MASKPROC)
1128 Str += "p";
1129 else if (Flag)
1130 Str += "x";
1131 }
1132 }
1133 return Str;
1134}

1136static const char *getElfSegmentType(unsigned Arch, unsigned Type) {
1137 // Check potentially overlapped processor-specific
1138 // program header type.
1139 switch (Arch) {
1140 case ELF::EM_ARM:
1141 switch (Type) { LLVM_READOBJ_ENUM_CASE(ELF, PT_ARM_EXIDX); }
1142 break;
1143 case ELF::EM_MIPS:
1144 case ELF::EM_MIPS_RS3_LE:
1145 switch (Type) {
1146 LLVM_READOBJ_ENUM_CASE(ELF, PT_MIPS_REGINFO);
1147 LLVM_READOBJ_ENUM_CASE(ELF, PT_MIPS_RTPROC);
1148 LLVM_READOBJ_ENUM_CASE(ELF, PT_MIPS_OPTIONS);
1149 LLVM_READOBJ_ENUM_CASE(ELF, PT_MIPS_ABIFLAGS);
1150 }
1151 break;
1152 }
1153
1154 switch (Type) {
1155 LLVM_READOBJ_ENUM_CASE(ELF, PT_NULL );
1156 LLVM_READOBJ_ENUM_CASE(ELF, PT_LOAD );
1157 LLVM_READOBJ_ENUM_CASE(ELF, PT_DYNAMIC);
1158 LLVM_READOBJ_ENUM_CASE(ELF, PT_INTERP );
1159 LLVM_READOBJ_ENUM_CASE(ELF, PT_NOTE );
1160 LLVM_READOBJ_ENUM_CASE(ELF, PT_SHLIB );
1161 LLVM_READOBJ_ENUM_CASE(ELF, PT_PHDR );
1162 LLVM_READOBJ_ENUM_CASE(ELF, PT_TLS );
1163
1164 LLVM_READOBJ_ENUM_CASE(ELF, PT_GNU_EH_FRAME);
1165 LLVM_READOBJ_ENUM_CASE(ELF, PT_SUNW_UNWIND);
1166
1167 LLVM_READOBJ_ENUM_CASE(ELF, PT_GNU_STACK);
1168 LLVM_READOBJ_ENUM_CASE(ELF, PT_GNU_RELRO);
1169
1170 LLVM_READOBJ_ENUM_CASE(ELF, PT_OPENBSD_RANDOMIZE);
1171 LLVM_READOBJ_ENUM_CASE(ELF, PT_OPENBSD_WXNEEDED);
1172 LLVM_READOBJ_ENUM_CASE(ELF, PT_OPENBSD_BOOTDATA);
1173
1174 default:
1175 return "";
1176 }

1179static std::string getElfPtType(unsigned Arch, unsigned Type) {
1180 switch (Type) {
1181 LLVM_READOBJ_PHDR_ENUM(ELF, PT_NULL)
1182 LLVM_READOBJ_PHDR_ENUM(ELF, PT_LOAD)
1183 LLVM_READOBJ_PHDR_ENUM(ELF, PT_DYNAMIC)
1184 LLVM_READOBJ_PHDR_ENUM(ELF, PT_INTERP)
1185 LLVM_READOBJ_PHDR_ENUM(ELF, PT_NOTE)
1186 LLVM_READOBJ_PHDR_ENUM(ELF, PT_SHLIB)
1187 LLVM_READOBJ_PHDR_ENUM(ELF, PT_PHDR)
1188 LLVM_READOBJ_PHDR_ENUM(ELF, PT_TLS)
1189 LLVM_READOBJ_PHDR_ENUM(ELF, PT_GNU_EH_FRAME)
1190 LLVM_READOBJ_PHDR_ENUM(ELF, PT_SUNW_UNWIND)
1191 LLVM_READOBJ_PHDR_ENUM(ELF, PT_GNU_STACK)
1192 LLVM_READOBJ_PHDR_ENUM(ELF, PT_GNU_RELRO)
1193 default:
1194 // All machine specific PT_* types
1195 switch (Arch) {
1196 case ELF::EM_ARM:
1197 if (Type == ELF::PT_ARM_EXIDX)
1198 return "EXIDX";
1199 break;
1200 case ELF::EM_MIPS:
1201 case ELF::EM_MIPS_RS3_LE:
1202 switch (Type) {
1203 case PT_MIPS_REGINFO:
1204 return "REGINFO";
1205 case PT_MIPS_RTPROC:
1206 return "RTPROC";
1207 case PT_MIPS_OPTIONS:
1208 return "OPTIONS";
1209 case PT_MIPS_ABIFLAGS:
1210 return "ABIFLAGS";
1211 }
1212 break;
1213 }
1214 }
1215 return std::string("<unknown>: ") + to_string(format_hex(Type, 1));
1216}

1358
1359template <typename ELFT>
1360void ELFDumper<ELFT>::loadDynamicTable(const ELFFile<ELFT> *Obj) {
1361 // Try to locate the PT_DYNAMIC header.
1362 const Elf_Phdr *DynamicPhdr = nullptr;
1363 for (const Elf_Phdr &Phdr : unwrapOrError(Obj->program_headers())) {
1364 if (Phdr.p_type != ELF::PT_DYNAMIC)
1365 continue;
1366 DynamicPhdr = &Phdr;
1367 break;
1368 }
1369
1370 // Try to locate the .dynamic section in the sections header table.
1371 const Elf_Shdr *DynamicSec = nullptr;
1372 for (const Elf_Shdr &Sec : unwrapOrError(Obj->sections())) {
1373 if (Sec.sh_type != ELF::SHT_DYNAMIC)
1374 continue;
1375 DynamicSec = &Sec;
1376 break;
1377 }
1378
1379 // Information in the section header has priority over the information
1380 // in a PT_DYNAMIC header.
1381 // Ignore sh_entsize and use the expected value for entry size explicitly.
1382 // This allows us to dump the dynamic sections with a broken sh_entsize
1383 // field.
1384 if (DynamicSec) {
1385 DynamicTable = checkDRI({ObjF->getELFFile()->base() + DynamicSec->sh_offset,
1386 DynamicSec->sh_size, sizeof(Elf_Dyn)});
1387 parseDynamicTable();
1388 }
1389
1390 // If we have a PT_DYNAMIC header, we will either check the found dynamic
1391 // section or take the dynamic table data directly from the header.
1392 if (!DynamicPhdr)
1393 return;
1394
1395 if (DynamicPhdr->p_offset + DynamicPhdr->p_filesz >
1396 ObjF->getMemoryBufferRef().getBufferSize())
1397 reportError(
1398 "PT_DYNAMIC segment offset + size exceeds the size of the file");
1399
1400 if (!DynamicSec) {
1401 DynamicTable = createDRIFrom(DynamicPhdr, sizeof(Elf_Dyn));
1402 parseDynamicTable();
1403 return;
1404 }
1405
1406 StringRef Name = unwrapOrError(Obj->getSectionName(DynamicSec));
1407 if (DynamicSec->sh_addr + DynamicSec->sh_size >
1408 DynamicPhdr->p_vaddr + DynamicPhdr->p_memsz ||
1409 DynamicSec->sh_addr < DynamicPhdr->p_vaddr)
1410 reportWarning("The SHT_DYNAMIC section '" + Name +
1411 "' is not contained within the "
1412 "PT_DYNAMIC segment");
1413
1414 if (DynamicSec->sh_addr != DynamicPhdr->p_vaddr)
1415 reportWarning("The SHT_DYNAMIC section '" + Name +
1416 "' is not at the start of "
1417 "PT_DYNAMIC segment");
1418}
1419
1420template <typename ELFT>
1421ELFDumper<ELFT>::ELFDumper(const object::ELFObjectFile<ELFT> *ObjF,
1422 ScopedPrinter &Writer)
1423 : ObjDumper(Writer), ObjF(ObjF) {
1424 const ELFFile<ELFT> *Obj = ObjF->getELFFile();
1425
1426 for (const Elf_Shdr &Sec : unwrapOrError(Obj->sections())) {
1427 switch (Sec.sh_type) {
1428 case ELF::SHT_SYMTAB:
1429 if (!DotSymtabSec)
1430 DotSymtabSec = &Sec;
1431 break;
1432 case ELF::SHT_DYNSYM:
1433 if (!DynSymRegion.Size) {
1434 DynSymRegion = createDRIFrom(&Sec);
1435 // This is only used (if Elf_Shdr present)for naming section in GNU
1436 // style
1437 DynSymtabName = unwrapOrError(Obj->getSectionName(&Sec));
1438
1439 if (Expected<StringRef> E = Obj->getStringTableForSymtab(Sec))
1440 DynamicStringTable = *E;
1441 else
1442 warn(E.takeError());
1443 }
1444 break;
1445 case ELF::SHT_SYMTAB_SHNDX:
1446 ShndxTable = unwrapOrError(Obj->getSHNDXTable(Sec));
1447 break;
1448 case ELF::SHT_GNU_versym:
1449 if (!SymbolVersionSection)
1450 SymbolVersionSection = &Sec;
1451 break;
1452 case ELF::SHT_GNU_verdef:
1453 if (!SymbolVersionDefSection)
1454 SymbolVersionDefSection = &Sec;
1455 break;
1456 case ELF::SHT_GNU_verneed:
1457 if (!SymbolVersionNeedSection)
1458 SymbolVersionNeedSection = &Sec;
1459 break;
1460 case ELF::SHT_LLVM_CALL_GRAPH_PROFILE:
1461 if (!DotCGProfileSec)
1462 DotCGProfileSec = &Sec;
1463 break;
1464 case ELF::SHT_LLVM_ADDRSIG:
1465 if (!DotAddrsigSec)
1466 DotAddrsigSec = &Sec;
1467 break;
1468 }
1469 }
1470
1471 loadDynamicTable(Obj);
1472
1473 if (opts::Output == opts::GNU)
1474 ELFDumperStyle.reset(new GNUStyle<ELFT>(Writer, this));
1475 else
1476 ELFDumperStyle.reset(new LLVMStyle<ELFT>(Writer, this));
1477}
1478
1479static const char *getTypeString(unsigned Arch, uint64_t Type) {
1480#define DYNAMIC_TAG(n, v)
1481 switch (Arch) {
1482
1483 case EM_AARCH64:
1484 switch (Type) {
1485#define AARCH64_DYNAMIC_TAG(name, value) \
1486 case DT_##name: \
1487 return #name;
1488#include "llvm/BinaryFormat/DynamicTags.def"
1489#undef AARCH64_DYNAMIC_TAG
1490 }
1491 break;
1492
1493 case EM_HEXAGON:
1494 switch (Type) {
1495#define HEXAGON_DYNAMIC_TAG(name, value) \
1496 case DT_##name: \
1497 return #name;
1498#include "llvm/BinaryFormat/DynamicTags.def"
1499#undef HEXAGON_DYNAMIC_TAG
1500 }
1501 break;
1502
1503 case EM_MIPS:
1504 switch (Type) {
1505#define MIPS_DYNAMIC_TAG(name, value) \
1506 case DT_##name: \
1507 return #name;
1508#include "llvm/BinaryFormat/DynamicTags.def"
1509#undef MIPS_DYNAMIC_TAG
1510 }
1511 break;
1512
1513 case EM_PPC64:
1514 switch (Type) {
1515#define PPC64_DYNAMIC_TAG(name, value) \
1516 case DT_##name: \
1517 return #name;
1518#include "llvm/BinaryFormat/DynamicTags.def"
1519#undef PPC64_DYNAMIC_TAG
1520 }
1521 break;
1522 }
1523#undef DYNAMIC_TAG
1524 switch (Type) {
1525// Now handle all dynamic tags except the architecture specific ones
1526#define AARCH64_DYNAMIC_TAG(name, value)
1527#define MIPS_DYNAMIC_TAG(name, value)
1528#define HEXAGON_DYNAMIC_TAG(name, value)
1529#define PPC64_DYNAMIC_TAG(name, value)
1530// Also ignore marker tags such as DT_HIOS (maps to DT_VERNEEDNUM), etc.
1531#define DYNAMIC_TAG_MARKER(name, value)
1532#define DYNAMIC_TAG(name, value) \
1533 case DT_##name: \
1534 return #name;
1535#include "llvm/BinaryFormat/DynamicTags.def"
1536#undef DYNAMIC_TAG
1537#undef AARCH64_DYNAMIC_TAG
1538#undef MIPS_DYNAMIC_TAG
1539#undef HEXAGON_DYNAMIC_TAG
1540#undef PPC64_DYNAMIC_TAG
1541#undef DYNAMIC_TAG_MARKER
1542 default:
1543 return "unknown";
1544 }
1545}
1546
1547template <typename ELFT> void ELFDumper<ELFT>::parseDynamicTable() {
1548 auto toMappedAddr = [&](uint64_t Tag, uint64_t VAddr) -> const uint8_t * {
1549 auto MappedAddrOrError = ObjF->getELFFile()->toMappedAddr(VAddr);
1550 if (!MappedAddrOrError) {
1551 reportWarning("Unable to parse DT_" +
1552 Twine(getTypeString(
1553 ObjF->getELFFile()->getHeader()->e_machine, Tag)) +
1554 ": " + llvm::toString(MappedAddrOrError.takeError()));
1555 return nullptr;
1556 }
1557 return MappedAddrOrError.get();
1558 };
1559
1560 uint64_t SONameOffset = 0;
1561 const char *StringTableBegin = nullptr;
1562 uint64_t StringTableSize = 0;
1563 for (const Elf_Dyn &Dyn : dynamic_table()) {
1564 switch (Dyn.d_tag) {
1565 case ELF::DT_HASH:
1566 HashTable = reinterpret_cast<const Elf_Hash *>(
1567 toMappedAddr(Dyn.getTag(), Dyn.getPtr()));
1568 break;
1569 case ELF::DT_GNU_HASH:
1570 GnuHashTable = reinterpret_cast<const Elf_GnuHash *>(
1571 toMappedAddr(Dyn.getTag(), Dyn.getPtr()));
1572 break;
1573 case ELF::DT_STRTAB:
1574 StringTableBegin = reinterpret_cast<const char *>(
1575 toMappedAddr(Dyn.getTag(), Dyn.getPtr()));
1576 break;
1577 case ELF::DT_STRSZ:
1578 StringTableSize = Dyn.getVal();
1579 break;
1580 case ELF::DT_SYMTAB:
1581 DynSymRegion.Addr = toMappedAddr(Dyn.getTag(), Dyn.getPtr());
1582 DynSymRegion.EntSize = sizeof(Elf_Sym);
1583 break;
1584 case ELF::DT_RELA:
1585 DynRelaRegion.Addr = toMappedAddr(Dyn.getTag(), Dyn.getPtr());
1586 break;
1587 case ELF::DT_RELASZ:
1588 DynRelaRegion.Size = Dyn.getVal();
1589 break;
1590 case ELF::DT_RELAENT:
1591 DynRelaRegion.EntSize = Dyn.getVal();
1592 break;
1593 case ELF::DT_SONAME:
1594 SONameOffset = Dyn.getVal();
1595 break;
1596 case ELF::DT_REL:
1597 DynRelRegion.Addr = toMappedAddr(Dyn.getTag(), Dyn.getPtr());
1598 break;
1599 case ELF::DT_RELSZ:
1600 DynRelRegion.Size = Dyn.getVal();
1601 break;
1602 case ELF::DT_RELENT:
1603 DynRelRegion.EntSize = Dyn.getVal();
1604 break;
1605 case ELF::DT_RELR:
1606 case ELF::DT_ANDROID_RELR:
1607 DynRelrRegion.Addr = toMappedAddr(Dyn.getTag(), Dyn.getPtr());
1608 break;
1609 case ELF::DT_RELRSZ:
1610 case ELF::DT_ANDROID_RELRSZ:
1611 DynRelrRegion.Size = Dyn.getVal();
1612 break;
1613 case ELF::DT_RELRENT:
1614 case ELF::DT_ANDROID_RELRENT:
1615 DynRelrRegion.EntSize = Dyn.getVal();
1616 break;
1617 case ELF::DT_PLTREL:
1618 if (Dyn.getVal() == DT_REL)
1619 DynPLTRelRegion.EntSize = sizeof(Elf_Rel);
1620 else if (Dyn.getVal() == DT_RELA)
1621 DynPLTRelRegion.EntSize = sizeof(Elf_Rela);
1622 else
1623 reportError(Twine("unknown DT_PLTREL value of ") +
1624 Twine((uint64_t)Dyn.getVal()));
1625 break;
1626 case ELF::DT_JMPREL:
1627 DynPLTRelRegion.Addr = toMappedAddr(Dyn.getTag(), Dyn.getPtr());
1628 break;
1629 case ELF::DT_PLTRELSZ:
1630 DynPLTRelRegion.Size = Dyn.getVal();
1631 break;
1632 }
1633 }
1634 if (StringTableBegin)
1635 DynamicStringTable = StringRef(StringTableBegin, StringTableSize);
1636 if (SONameOffset)
1637 SOName = getDynamicString(SONameOffset);
1638}

1786template <typename T, typename TFlag>
1787void printFlags(T Value, ArrayRef<EnumEntry<TFlag>> Flags, raw_ostream &OS) {
1788 using FlagEntry = EnumEntry<TFlag>;
1789 using FlagVector = SmallVector<FlagEntry, 10>;
1790 FlagVector SetFlags;
1791
1792 for (const auto &Flag : Flags) {
1793 if (Flag.Value == 0)
1794 continue;
1795
1796 if ((Value & Flag.Value) == Flag.Value)
1797 SetFlags.push_back(Flag);
1798 }
1799
1800 T RemainingBits = Value;
1801 for (const auto &Flag : SetFlags) {
1802 OS << Flag.Name << " ";
1803 RemainingBits &= ~Flag.Value;
1804 }
1805 if (RemainingBits) {
1806 OS << "| 0x" << utohexstr(RemainingBits, false);
1807 }
1808}

1810template <class ELFT>
1811StringRef ELFDumper<ELFT>::getDynamicString(uint64_t Value) const {
1812 if (Value >= DynamicStringTable.size())
1813 reportError("Invalid dynamic string table reference");
1814 return StringRef(DynamicStringTable.data() + Value);
1815}

1817static void printLibrary(raw_ostream &OS, const Twine &Tag, const Twine &Name) {
1818 OS << Tag << ": [" << Name << "]";
1819}
1820
1821template <class ELFT>
1822void ELFDumper<ELFT>::printDynamicEntry(raw_ostream &OS, uint64_t Type,
1823 uint64_t Value) const {
1824 const char *ConvChar =
1825 (opts::Output == opts::GNU) ? "0x%" PRIx64 : "0x%" PRIX64;
1826
1827 // Handle custom printing of architecture specific tags
1828 switch (ObjF->getELFFile()->getHeader()->e_machine) {
1829 case EM_AARCH64:
1830 switch (Type) {
1831 case DT_AARCH64_BTI_PLT:
1832 case DT_AARCH64_PAC_PLT:
1833 OS << Value;
1834 return;
1835 default:
1836 break;
1837 }
1838 break;
1839 case EM_HEXAGON:
1840 switch (Type) {
1841 case DT_HEXAGON_VER:
1842 OS << Value;
1843 return;
1844 case DT_HEXAGON_SYMSZ:
1845 case DT_HEXAGON_PLT:
1846 OS << format(ConvChar, Value);
1847 return;
1848 default:
1849 break;
1850 }
1851 break;
1852 case EM_MIPS:
1853 switch (Type) {
1854 case DT_MIPS_RLD_VERSION:
1855 case DT_MIPS_LOCAL_GOTNO:
1856 case DT_MIPS_SYMTABNO:
1857 case DT_MIPS_UNREFEXTNO:
1858 OS << Value;
1859 return;
1860 case DT_MIPS_TIME_STAMP:
1861 case DT_MIPS_ICHECKSUM:
1862 case DT_MIPS_IVERSION:
1863 case DT_MIPS_BASE_ADDRESS:
1864 case DT_MIPS_MSYM:
1865 case DT_MIPS_CONFLICT:
1866 case DT_MIPS_LIBLIST:
1867 case DT_MIPS_CONFLICTNO:
1868 case DT_MIPS_LIBLISTNO:
1869 case DT_MIPS_GOTSYM:
1870 case DT_MIPS_HIPAGENO:
1871 case DT_MIPS_RLD_MAP:
1872 case DT_MIPS_DELTA_CLASS:
1873 case DT_MIPS_DELTA_CLASS_NO:
1874 case DT_MIPS_DELTA_INSTANCE:
1875 case DT_MIPS_DELTA_RELOC:
1876 case DT_MIPS_DELTA_RELOC_NO:
1877 case DT_MIPS_DELTA_SYM:
1878 case DT_MIPS_DELTA_SYM_NO:
1879 case DT_MIPS_DELTA_CLASSSYM:
1880 case DT_MIPS_DELTA_CLASSSYM_NO:
1881 case DT_MIPS_CXX_FLAGS:
1882 case DT_MIPS_PIXIE_INIT:
1883 case DT_MIPS_SYMBOL_LIB:
1884 case DT_MIPS_LOCALPAGE_GOTIDX:
1885 case DT_MIPS_LOCAL_GOTIDX:
1886 case DT_MIPS_HIDDEN_GOTIDX:
1887 case DT_MIPS_PROTECTED_GOTIDX:
1888 case DT_MIPS_OPTIONS:
1889 case DT_MIPS_INTERFACE:
1890 case DT_MIPS_DYNSTR_ALIGN:
1891 case DT_MIPS_INTERFACE_SIZE:
1892 case DT_MIPS_RLD_TEXT_RESOLVE_ADDR:
1893 case DT_MIPS_PERF_SUFFIX:
1894 case DT_MIPS_COMPACT_SIZE:
1895 case DT_MIPS_GP_VALUE:
1896 case DT_MIPS_AUX_DYNAMIC:
1897 case DT_MIPS_PLTGOT:
1898 case DT_MIPS_RWPLT:
1899 case DT_MIPS_RLD_MAP_REL:
1900 OS << format(ConvChar, Value);
1901 return;
1902 case DT_MIPS_FLAGS:
1903 printFlags(Value, makeArrayRef(ElfDynamicDTMipsFlags), OS);
1904 return;
1905 case DT_MIPS_CHERI_FLAGS:
1906 switch (Value & DF_MIPS_CHERI_ABI_MASK) {
1907 case DF_MIPS_CHERI_ABI_LEGACY: OS << "ABI_LEGACY"; break;
1908 case DF_MIPS_CHERI_ABI_PCREL: OS << "ABI_PCREL"; break;
1909 case DF_MIPS_CHERI_ABI_PLT: OS << "ABI_PLT"; break;
1910 case DF_MIPS_CHERI_ABI_FNDESC: OS << "ABI_FNDESC"; break;
1911 }
1912 Value &= ~DF_MIPS_CHERI_ABI_MASK;
1913 if (Value) {
1914 OS << ' ';
1915 printFlags(Value, makeArrayRef(ElfDynamicDTMipsCheriAbiFlags), OS);
1916 }
1917 return;
1918 default:
1919 break;
1920 }
1921 break;
1922 default:
1923 break;
1924 }
1925
1926 switch (Type) {
1927 case DT_PLTREL:
1928 if (Value == DT_REL) {
1929 OS << "REL";
1930 break;
1931 } else if (Value == DT_RELA) {
1932 OS << "RELA";
1933 break;
1934 }
1935 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
1936 case DT_PLTGOT:
1937 case DT_HASH:
1938 case DT_STRTAB:
1939 case DT_SYMTAB:
1940 case DT_RELA:
1941 case DT_INIT:
1942 case DT_FINI:
1943 case DT_REL:
1944 case DT_JMPREL:
1945 case DT_INIT_ARRAY:
1946 case DT_FINI_ARRAY:
1947 case DT_PREINIT_ARRAY:
1948 case DT_DEBUG:
1949 case DT_VERDEF:
1950 case DT_VERNEED:
1951 case DT_VERSYM:
1952 case DT_GNU_HASH:
1953 case DT_NULL:
1954 OS << format(ConvChar, Value);
1955 break;
1956 case DT_RELACOUNT:
1957 case DT_RELCOUNT:
1958 case DT_VERDEFNUM:
1959 case DT_VERNEEDNUM:
1960 OS << Value;
1961 break;
1962 case DT_PLTRELSZ:
1963 case DT_RELASZ:
1964 case DT_RELAENT:
1965 case DT_STRSZ:
1966 case DT_SYMENT:
1967 case DT_RELSZ:
1968 case DT_RELENT:
1969 case DT_INIT_ARRAYSZ:
1970 case DT_FINI_ARRAYSZ:
1971 case DT_PREINIT_ARRAYSZ:
1972 case DT_ANDROID_RELSZ:
1973 case DT_ANDROID_RELASZ:
1974 OS << Value << " (bytes)";
1975 break;
1976 case DT_NEEDED:
1977 printLibrary(OS, "Shared library", getDynamicString(Value));
1978 break;
1979 case DT_SONAME:
1980 printLibrary(OS, "Library soname", getDynamicString(Value));
1981 break;
1982 case DT_AUXILIARY:
1983 printLibrary(OS, "Auxiliary library", getDynamicString(Value));
1984 break;
1985 case DT_USED:
1986 printLibrary(OS, "Not needed object", getDynamicString(Value));
1987 break;
1988 case DT_FILTER:
1989 printLibrary(OS, "Filter library", getDynamicString(Value));
1990 break;
1991 case DT_RPATH:
1992 case DT_RUNPATH:
1993 OS << getDynamicString(Value);
1994 break;
1995 case DT_FLAGS:
1996 printFlags(Value, makeArrayRef(ElfDynamicDTFlags), OS);
1997 break;
1998 case DT_FLAGS_1:
1999 printFlags(Value, makeArrayRef(ElfDynamicDTFlags1), OS);
2000 break;
2001 default:
2002 OS << format(ConvChar, Value);
2003 break;
2004 }
2005}

2031template <class ELFT> void ELFDumper<ELFT>::printNeededLibraries() {
2032 ListScope D(W, "NeededLibraries");
2033
2034 using LibsTy = std::vector<StringRef>;
2035 LibsTy Libs;
2036
2037 for (const auto &Entry : dynamic_table())
2038 if (Entry.d_tag == ELF::DT_NEEDED)
2039 Libs.push_back(getDynamicString(Entry.d_un.d_val));
2040
2041 llvm::stable_sort(Libs);
2042
2043 for (const auto &L : Libs)
2044 W.startLine() << L << "\n";
2045}

2047template <typename ELFT> void ELFDumper<ELFT>::printHashTable() {
2048 DictScope D(W, "HashTable");
2049 if (!HashTable)
2050 return;
2051 W.printNumber("Num Buckets", HashTable->nbucket);
2052 W.printNumber("Num Chains", HashTable->nchain);
2053 W.printList("Buckets", HashTable->buckets());
2054 W.printList("Chains", HashTable->chains());
2055}
2056
2057template <typename ELFT> void ELFDumper<ELFT>::printGnuHashTable() {
2058 DictScope D(W, "GnuHashTable");
2059 if (!GnuHashTable)
2060 return;
2061 W.printNumber("Num Buckets", GnuHashTable->nbuckets);
2062 W.printNumber("First Hashed Symbol Index", GnuHashTable->symndx);
2063 W.printNumber("Num Mask Words", GnuHashTable->maskwords);
2064 W.printNumber("Shift Count", GnuHashTable->shift2);
2065 W.printHexList("Bloom Filter", GnuHashTable->filter());
2066 W.printList("Buckets", GnuHashTable->buckets());
2067 Elf_Sym_Range Syms = dynamic_symbols();
2068 unsigned NumSyms = std::distance(Syms.begin(), Syms.end());
2069 if (!NumSyms)
2070 reportError("No dynamic symbol section");
2071 W.printHexList("Values", GnuHashTable->values(NumSyms));
2072}

2081
2082namespace {
2083
2084template <> void ELFDumper<ELF32LE>::printAttributes() {
2085 const ELFFile<ELF32LE> *Obj = ObjF->getELFFile();
2086 if (Obj->getHeader()->e_machine != EM_ARM) {
2087 W.startLine() << "Attributes not implemented.\n";
2088 return;
2089 }
2090
2091 DictScope BA(W, "BuildAttributes");
2092 for (const ELFO::Elf_Shdr &Sec : unwrapOrError(Obj->sections())) {
2093 if (Sec.sh_type != ELF::SHT_ARM_ATTRIBUTES)
2094 continue;
2095
2096 ArrayRef<uint8_t> Contents = unwrapOrError(Obj->getSectionContents(&Sec));
2097 if (Contents[0] != ARMBuildAttrs::Format_Version) {
2098 errs() << "unrecognised FormatVersion: 0x"
2099 << Twine::utohexstr(Contents[0]) << '\n';
2100 continue;
2101 }
2102
2103 W.printHex("FormatVersion", Contents[0]);
2104 if (Contents.size() == 1)
2105 continue;
2106
2107 ARMAttributeParser(&W).Parse(Contents, true);
2108 }
2109}

2120 MipsGOTParser(const ELFO *Obj, Elf_Dyn_Range DynTable, Elf_Sym_Range DynSyms);

2130 const Entry *getPltModulePointer() const;

2135 Entries getPltEntries() const;
2136
2137 uint64_t getGotAddress(const Entry * E) const;
2138 int64_t getGotOffset(const Entry * E) const;
2139 const Elf_Sym *getGotSym(const Entry *E) const;
2140
2141 uint64_t getPltAddress(const Entry * E) const;
2142 const Elf_Sym *getPltSym(const Entry *E) const;
2143
2144 StringRef getPltStrTable() const { return PltStrTable; }
2145
2146private:
2147 const Elf_Shdr *GotSec;
2148 size_t LocalNum;
2149 size_t GlobalNum;
2150
2151 const Elf_Shdr *PltSec;
2152 const Elf_Shdr *PltRelSec;
2153 const Elf_Shdr *PltSymTable;
2154 Elf_Sym_Range GotDynSyms;
2155 StringRef PltStrTable;
2156
2157 Entries GotEntries;
2158 Entries PltEntries;
2159};
2160
2161} // end anonymous namespace
2162
2163template <class ELFT>
2164MipsGOTParser<ELFT>::MipsGOTParser(const ELFO *Obj, Elf_Dyn_Range DynTable,
2165 Elf_Sym_Range DynSyms)
2166 : IsStatic(DynTable.empty()), Obj(Obj), GotSec(nullptr), LocalNum(0),
2167 GlobalNum(0), PltSec(nullptr), PltRelSec(nullptr), PltSymTable(nullptr) {
2168 // See "Global Offset Table" in Chapter 5 in the following document
2169 // for detailed GOT description.
2170 // ftp://www.linux-mips.org/pub/linux/mips/doc/ABI/mipsabi.pdf
2171
2172 // Find static GOT secton.
2173 if (IsStatic) {
2174 GotSec = findSectionByName(*Obj, ".got");
2175 if (!GotSec)
2176 reportError("Cannot find .got section");
2177
2178 ArrayRef<uint8_t> Content = unwrapOrError(Obj->getSectionContents(GotSec));
2179 GotEntries = Entries(reinterpret_cast<const Entry *>(Content.data()),
2180 Content.size() / sizeof(Entry));
2181 LocalNum = GotEntries.size();
2182 return;
2183 }
2184
2185 // Lookup dynamic table tags which define GOT/PLT layouts.
2186 Optional<uint64_t> DtPltGot;
2187 Optional<uint64_t> DtLocalGotNum;
2188 Optional<uint64_t> DtGotSym;
2189 Optional<uint64_t> DtMipsPltGot;
2190 Optional<uint64_t> DtJmpRel;
2191 for (const auto &Entry : DynTable) {
2192 switch (Entry.getTag()) {
2193 case ELF::DT_PLTGOT:
2194 DtPltGot = Entry.getVal();
2195 break;
2196 case ELF::DT_MIPS_LOCAL_GOTNO:
2197 DtLocalGotNum = Entry.getVal();
2198 break;
2199 case ELF::DT_MIPS_GOTSYM:
2200 DtGotSym = Entry.getVal();
2201 break;
2202 case ELF::DT_MIPS_PLTGOT:
2203 DtMipsPltGot = Entry.getVal();
2204 break;
2205 case ELF::DT_JMPREL:
2206 DtJmpRel = Entry.getVal();
2207 break;
2208 }
2209 }
2210
2211 // Find dynamic GOT section.
2212 if (DtPltGot || DtLocalGotNum || DtGotSym) {
2213 if (!DtPltGot)
2214 report_fatal_error("Cannot find PLTGOT dynamic table tag.");
2215 if (!DtLocalGotNum)
2216 report_fatal_error("Cannot find MIPS_LOCAL_GOTNO dynamic table tag.");
2217 if (!DtGotSym)
2218 report_fatal_error("Cannot find MIPS_GOTSYM dynamic table tag.");
2219
2220 size_t DynSymTotal = DynSyms.size();
2221 if (*DtGotSym > DynSymTotal)
2222 reportError("MIPS_GOTSYM exceeds a number of dynamic symbols");
2223
2224 GotSec = findNotEmptySectionByAddress(Obj, *DtPltGot);
2225 if (!GotSec)
2226 reportError("There is no not empty GOT section at 0x" +
2227 Twine::utohexstr(*DtPltGot));
2228
2229 LocalNum = *DtLocalGotNum;
2230 GlobalNum = DynSymTotal - *DtGotSym;
2231
2232 ArrayRef<uint8_t> Content = unwrapOrError(Obj->getSectionContents(GotSec));
2233 GotEntries = Entries(reinterpret_cast<const Entry *>(Content.data()),
2234 Content.size() / sizeof(Entry));
2235 GotDynSyms = DynSyms.drop_front(*DtGotSym);
2236 }
2237
2238 // Find PLT section.
2239 if (DtMipsPltGot || DtJmpRel) {
2240 if (!DtMipsPltGot)
2241 report_fatal_error("Cannot find MIPS_PLTGOT dynamic table tag.");
2242 if (!DtJmpRel)
2243 report_fatal_error("Cannot find JMPREL dynamic table tag.");
2244
2245 PltSec = findNotEmptySectionByAddress(Obj, *DtMipsPltGot);
2246 if (!PltSec)
2247 report_fatal_error("There is no not empty PLTGOT section at 0x " +
2248 Twine::utohexstr(*DtMipsPltGot));
2249
2250 PltRelSec = findNotEmptySectionByAddress(Obj, *DtJmpRel);
2251 if (!PltRelSec)
2252 report_fatal_error("There is no not empty RELPLT section at 0x" +
2253 Twine::utohexstr(*DtJmpRel));
2254
2255 ArrayRef<uint8_t> PltContent =
2256 unwrapOrError(Obj->getSectionContents(PltSec));
2257 PltEntries = Entries(reinterpret_cast<const Entry *>(PltContent.data()),
2258 PltContent.size() / sizeof(Entry));
2259
2260 PltSymTable = unwrapOrError(Obj->getSection(PltRelSec->sh_link));
2261 PltStrTable = unwrapOrError(Obj->getStringTableForSymtab(*PltSymTable));
2262 }
2263}
2264
2265template <class ELFT> uint64_t MipsGOTParser<ELFT>::getGp() const {
2266 return GotSec->sh_addr + 0x7ff0;
2267}
2268
2269template <class ELFT>
2270const typename MipsGOTParser<ELFT>::Entry *
2271MipsGOTParser<ELFT>::getGotLazyResolver() const {
2272 return LocalNum > 0 ? &GotEntries[0] : nullptr;
2273}
2274
2275template <class ELFT>
2276const typename MipsGOTParser<ELFT>::Entry *
2277MipsGOTParser<ELFT>::getGotModulePointer() const {
2278 if (LocalNum < 2)
2279 return nullptr;
2280 const Entry &E = GotEntries[1];
2281 if ((E >> (sizeof(Entry) * 8 - 1)) == 0)
2282 return nullptr;
2283 return &E;
2284}
2285
2286template <class ELFT>
2287typename MipsGOTParser<ELFT>::Entries
2288MipsGOTParser<ELFT>::getLocalEntries() const {
2289 size_t Skip = getGotModulePointer() ? 2 : 1;
2290 if (LocalNum - Skip <= 0)
2291 return Entries();
2292 return GotEntries.slice(Skip, LocalNum - Skip);
2293}
2294
2295template <class ELFT>
2296typename MipsGOTParser<ELFT>::Entries
2297MipsGOTParser<ELFT>::getGlobalEntries() const {
2298 if (GlobalNum == 0)
2299 return Entries();
2300 return GotEntries.slice(LocalNum, GlobalNum);
2301}
2302
2303template <class ELFT>
2304typename MipsGOTParser<ELFT>::Entries
2305MipsGOTParser<ELFT>::getOtherEntries() const {
2306 size_t OtherNum = GotEntries.size() - LocalNum - GlobalNum;
2307 if (OtherNum == 0)
2308 return Entries();
2309 return GotEntries.slice(LocalNum + GlobalNum, OtherNum);
2310}

2312template <class ELFT>
2313uint64_t MipsGOTParser<ELFT>::getGotAddress(const Entry *E) const {
2314 int64_t Offset = std::distance(GotEntries.data(), E) * sizeof(Entry);
2315 return GotSec->sh_addr + Offset;
2316}

2318template <class ELFT>
2319int64_t MipsGOTParser<ELFT>::getGotOffset(const Entry *E) const {
2320 int64_t Offset = std::distance(GotEntries.data(), E) * sizeof(Entry);
2321 return Offset - 0x7ff0;
2322}
2323
2324template <class ELFT>
2325const typename MipsGOTParser<ELFT>::Elf_Sym *
2326MipsGOTParser<ELFT>::getGotSym(const Entry *E) const {
2327 int64_t Offset = std::distance(GotEntries.data(), E);
2328 return &GotDynSyms[Offset - LocalNum];
2329}

2333MipsGOTParser<ELFT>::getPltLazyResolver() const {
2334 return PltEntries.empty() ? nullptr : &PltEntries[0];
2335}

2338const typename MipsGOTParser<ELFT>::Entry *
2339MipsGOTParser<ELFT>::getPltModulePointer() const {
2340 return PltEntries.size() < 2 ? nullptr : &PltEntries[1];
2341}

2344typename MipsGOTParser<ELFT>::Entries
2345MipsGOTParser<ELFT>::getPltEntries() const {
2346 if (PltEntries.size() <= 2)
2347 return Entries();
2348 return PltEntries.slice(2, PltEntries.size() - 2);
2349}

2351template <class ELFT>
2352uint64_t MipsGOTParser<ELFT>::getPltAddress(const Entry *E) const {
2353 int64_t Offset = std::distance(PltEntries.data(), E) * sizeof(Entry);
2354 return PltSec->sh_addr + Offset;
2355}
2356
2357template <class ELFT>
2358const typename MipsGOTParser<ELFT>::Elf_Sym *
2359MipsGOTParser<ELFT>::getPltSym(const Entry *E) const {
2360 int64_t Offset = std::distance(getPltEntries().data(), E);
2361 if (PltRelSec->sh_type == ELF::SHT_REL) {
2362 Elf_Rel_Range Rels = unwrapOrError(Obj->rels(PltRelSec));
2363 return unwrapOrError(Obj->getRelocationSymbol(&Rels[Offset], PltSymTable));
2364 } else {
2365 Elf_Rela_Range Rels = unwrapOrError(Obj->relas(PltRelSec));
2366 return unwrapOrError(Obj->getRelocationSymbol(&Rels[Offset], PltSymTable));
2367 }
2368}

2445static int getMipsRegisterSize(uint8_t Flag) {
2446 switch (Flag) {
2447 case Mips::AFL_REG_NONE:
2448 return 0;
2449 case Mips::AFL_REG_32:
2450 return 32;
2451 case Mips::AFL_REG_64:

2454 return 128;
2455 default:
2456 return -1;
2457 }

2460template <class ELFT> void ELFDumper<ELFT>::printMipsABIFlags() {
2461 const ELFFile<ELFT> *Obj = ObjF->getELFFile();
2462 const Elf_Shdr *Shdr = findSectionByName(*Obj, ".MIPS.abiflags");
2463 if (!Shdr) {
2464 W.startLine() << "There is no .MIPS.abiflags section in the file.\n";
2465 return;
2466 }
2467 ArrayRef<uint8_t> Sec = unwrapOrError(Obj->getSectionContents(Shdr));
2468 if (Sec.size() != sizeof(Elf_Mips_ABIFlags<ELFT>)) {
2469 W.startLine() << "The .MIPS.abiflags section has a wrong size.\n";
2470 return;
2471 }
2472
2473 auto *Flags = reinterpret_cast<const Elf_Mips_ABIFlags<ELFT> *>(Sec.data());
2474
2475 raw_ostream &OS = W.getOStream();
2476 DictScope GS(W, "MIPS ABI Flags");
2477
2478 W.printNumber("Version", Flags->version);
2479 W.startLine() << "ISA: ";
2480 if (Flags->isa_rev <= 1)
2481 OS << format("MIPS%u", Flags->isa_level);
2482 else
2483 OS << format("MIPS%ur%u", Flags->isa_level, Flags->isa_rev);
2484 OS << "\n";
2485 W.printEnum("ISA Extension", Flags->isa_ext, makeArrayRef(ElfMipsISAExtType));
2486 W.printFlags("ASEs", Flags->ases, makeArrayRef(ElfMipsASEFlags));
2487 W.printEnum("FP ABI", Flags->fp_abi, makeArrayRef(ElfMipsFpABIType));
2488 W.printNumber("GPR size", getMipsRegisterSize(Flags->gpr_size));
2489 W.printNumber("CPR1 size", getMipsRegisterSize(Flags->cpr1_size));
2490 W.printNumber("CPR2 size", getMipsRegisterSize(Flags->cpr2_size));
2491 W.printFlags("Flags 1", Flags->flags1, makeArrayRef(ElfMipsFlags1));
2492 W.printHex("Flags 2", Flags->flags2);
2493}

2495static const EnumEntry<uint64_t> CapRelocsPermsFlags[] = {
2496 {"Function", 0x8000000000000000ULL}};
2497
2498template <class ELFT> void ELFDumper<ELFT>::printCheriCapRelocs() {
2499 const ELFFile<ELFT> *Obj = ObjF->getELFFile();
2500 const Elf_Shdr *Shdr = findSectionByName(*Obj, "__cap_relocs");
2501 if (!Shdr) {
2502 W.startLine() << "There is no __cap_relocs section in the file.\n";
2503 return;
2504 }
2505 // TODO: get symbol name for __cap_reloc
2506 ArrayRef<uint8_t> Data = unwrapOrError(Obj->getSectionContents(Shdr));
2507 const uint64_t CapRelocsFileOffset = Shdr->sh_offset;
2508 const uint64_t CapRelocsEnd = Shdr->sh_offset + Shdr->sh_size;
2509 const size_t entry_size = ELFT::Is64Bits ? 40 : 20;
2510 if (Data.size() % entry_size != 0) {
2511 W.startLine() << "The __cap_relocs section has a wrong size: "
2512 << Data.size() << "\n";
2513 return;
2514 }
2515 ListScope L(W, "CHERI __cap_relocs");
2516#if 0
2517 errs() << "Cap relocs section from 0x" << utohexstr(CapRelocsFileOffset)
2518 << " to 0x" << utohexstr(CapRelocsEnd)
2519 << " size =" << (CapRelocsEnd - CapRelocsFileOffset) << "\n";
2520#endif
2521 // Create a map of all dynamic relocations that point into the
2522 // __cap_relocs section to add a symbol name to unresolved values
2523 // FIXME: this hardcodes REL so won't work for architectures that use RELA
2524 using Elf_Rel = typename ELFT::Rel;
2525 // typedef Elf64_Rel Elf_Rel;
2526 DenseMap<uint64_t, Elf_Rel> CapRelocsDynRels;
2527 for (const Elf_Rel &R : dyn_rels()) {
2528 if (R.r_offset >= CapRelocsFileOffset && R.r_offset < CapRelocsEnd) {
2529 // No need to store relocations aginst symbol zero since they don't have
2530 // a name
2531 if (R.getSymbol(Obj->isMips64EL()) != 0)
2532 CapRelocsDynRels.insert(std::make_pair((uint64_t)R.r_offset, R));
2533 }
2534 }
2535
2536 // Use the .symtab section if available otherwise use .dynsym:
2537 typename ELFT::SymRange Syms;
2538 StringRef StrTable;
2539 bool UsingDynsym = false;
2540 if (DotSymtabSec) {
2541 StrTable = unwrapOrError(Obj->getStringTableForSymtab(*DotSymtabSec));
2542 Syms = unwrapOrError(Obj->symbols(DotSymtabSec));
2543 } else {
2544 StrTable = DynamicStringTable;
2545 Syms = dynamic_symbols();
2546 UsingDynsym = true;
2547 }
2548 std::unordered_map<uint64_t, std::string> SymbolNames;
2549 for (const auto &Sym : Syms) {
2550 uint64_t Start = Sym.st_value;
2551 if (!Start)
2552 continue;
2553 std::string Name = getFullSymbolName(&Sym, StrTable, UsingDynsym);
2554 SymbolNames.insert({Start, Name});
2555 }
2556 // errs() << "Found " << CapRelocsDynRels.size()
2557 // << " dynamic relocations pointing to __cap_relocs section\n";
2558
2559 typename ELFT::SymRange DynSyms = dynamic_symbols();
2560 using TargetUint = typename ELFT::uint;
2561 using TargetInt =
2562 typename std::conditional<ELFT::Is64Bits, int64_t, int32_t>::type;
2563 for (int i = 0, e = Data.size() / entry_size; i < e; i++) {
2564 const uint64_t CurrentOffset = entry_size * i;
2565 const uint8_t *entry = Data.data() + CurrentOffset;
2566 uint64_t Target =
2567 support::endian::read<TargetUint, ELFT::TargetEndianness, 1>(
2568 entry);
2569 uint64_t Base =
2570 support::endian::read<TargetUint, ELFT::TargetEndianness, 1>(
2571 entry + sizeof(TargetUint));
2572 int64_t Offset =
2573 support::endian::read<TargetInt, ELFT::TargetEndianness, 1>(
2574 entry + 2*sizeof(TargetUint));
2575 uint64_t Length =
2576 support::endian::read<TargetUint, ELFT::TargetEndianness, 1>(
2577 entry + 3*sizeof(TargetUint));
2578 uint64_t Perms =
2579 support::endian::read<TargetUint, ELFT::TargetEndianness, 1>(
2580 entry + 4*sizeof(TargetUint));
2581 bool isFunction = Perms & (UINT64_C(1) << ((sizeof(TargetUint) * 8) - 1));
2582 bool isReadOnly = Perms & (UINT64_C(1) << ((sizeof(TargetUint) * 8) - 2));
2583 const char *PermStr =
2584 isFunction ? "Function" : (isReadOnly ? "Constant" : "Object");
2585 // Perms &= 0xffffffff;
2586 StringRef BaseSymbol = "<unknown symbol>";
2587 if (Base == 0) {
2588 // Base is 0 -> either it is really NULL or (more likely) there is a
2589 // dynamic relocation that will set the real address
2590 auto it = CapRelocsDynRels.find(CapRelocsFileOffset + CurrentOffset + 8);
2591 if (it != CapRelocsDynRels.end()) {
2592 Elf_Rel R = it->second;
2593 uint32_t SymIndex = R.getSymbol(Obj->isMips64EL());
2594 const Elf_Sym *Sym = unwrapOrError(getSymbol<ELFT>(DynSyms, SymIndex));
2595 BaseSymbol = unwrapOrError(Sym->getName(getDynamicStringTable()));
2596 // errs() << "Found dyn_rel for base: 0x" << utohexstr(R.r_offset) << "
2597 // Name=" << SymbolName << "\n";
2598 }
2599 } else {
2600 if (SymbolNames.find(Base) != SymbolNames.end())
2601 BaseSymbol = SymbolNames[Base];
2602 }
2603 StringRef LocationSym;
2604 if (SymbolNames.find(Target) != SymbolNames.end())
2605 LocationSym = SymbolNames[Target];
2606 // TODO: If base == 0 find the dynamic relocation target
2607 if (opts::ExpandRelocs) {
2608 DictScope L(W, "Relocation");
2609 raw_ostream &OS = W.startLine();
2610 OS << "Location: 0x" << utohexstr(Target);
2611 if (!LocationSym.empty())
2612 OS << " (" << LocationSym << ")";
2613 OS << "\n";
2614 W.printHex("Base", BaseSymbol, Base);
2615 W.printNumber("Offset", Offset);
2616 W.printNumber("Length", Length);
2617 W.printHex("Permissions", PermStr, Perms);
2618 } else {
2619 raw_ostream &OS = W.startLine();
2620 OS << format(" 0x%06lx", static_cast<unsigned long>(Target));
2621 if (!LocationSym.empty())
2622 OS << left_justify((" (" + LocationSym + ")").str(), 16);
2623 OS << format(" Base: 0x%lx (", static_cast<unsigned long>(Base))
2624 << BaseSymbol;
2625 if (Offset >= 0)
2626 OS << "+";
2627 OS << Offset;
2628 OS << format(") Length: %ld", static_cast<unsigned long>(Length));
2629 OS << " Perms: " << PermStr;
2630 OS << "\n";
2631 }
2632 }
2633}
2634
2635template <class ELFT> void ELFDumper<ELFT>::printCheriCapTable() {
2636 const ELFFile<ELFT> *Obj = ObjF->getELFFile();
2637 const Elf_Shdr *Shdr = findSectionByName(*Obj, ".captable");
2638 if (!Shdr) {
2639 W.startLine() << "There is no .captable section in the file.\n";
2640 return;
2641 }
2642 ListScope L(W, "CHERI .captable");
2643
2644 const Elf_Ehdr *e = Obj->getHeader();
2645 unsigned CapSize;
2646 if ((e->e_flags & EF_MIPS_MACH) == EF_MIPS_MACH_CHERI256) {
2647 CapSize = 32;
2648 } else if ((e->e_flags & EF_MIPS_MACH) == EF_MIPS_MACH_CHERI128) {
2649 CapSize = 16;
2650 } else {
2651 W.startLine() << "Invalid ELF header (no EF_MIPS_MACH_CHERI128/256 flag)\n";
2652 return;
2653 }
2654 const uint64_t CapTableStartVaddr = Shdr->sh_addr;
2655 const uint64_t CapTableEndVaddr = Shdr->sh_addr + Shdr->sh_size;
2656
2657 // Use the .symtab section if available otherwise use .dynsym:
2658 typename ELFT::SymRange Syms;
2659 StringRef StrTable;
2660 bool UsingDynsym = false;
2661 if (DotSymtabSec) {
2662 StrTable = unwrapOrError(Obj->getStringTableForSymtab(*DotSymtabSec));
2663 Syms = unwrapOrError(Obj->symbols(DotSymtabSec));
2664 } else {
2665 StrTable = DynamicStringTable;
2666 Syms = dynamic_symbols();
2667 UsingDynsym = true;
2668 }
2669
2670 std::unordered_map<uint64_t, std::string> SymbolNames;
2671 for (const auto &Sym : Syms) {
2672 uint64_t Start = Sym.st_value;
2673 if (Start < CapTableStartVaddr || Start > CapTableEndVaddr)
2674 continue;
2675 std::string Name = getFullSymbolName(&Sym, StrTable, UsingDynsym);
2676 if (Name == "_CHERI_CAPABILITY_TABLE_")
2677 continue;
2678 SymbolNames.insert({Start, Name});
2679 }
2680
2681 // Create a map of all dynamic relocations that point into the
2682 // __cap_relocs section to add a symbol name to unresolved values
2683 // FIXME: this hardcodes REL so won't work for architectures that use RELA
2684 using Elf_Rel = typename ELFT::Rel;
2685 // typedef Elf64_Rel Elf_Rel;
2686 DenseMap<uint64_t, Elf_Rela> CapTableDynRels;
2687
2688 auto FindRelocs = [&](const DynRegionInfo &RelRegion) {
2689 if (RelRegion.Size == 0)
2690 return;
2691 if (RelRegion.EntSize == sizeof(Elf_Rela)) {
2692 for (const Elf_Rela &Rela : RelRegion.getAsArrayRef<Elf_Rela>()) {
2693 if (Rela.r_offset >= CapTableStartVaddr &&
2694 Rela.r_offset < CapTableEndVaddr)
2695 CapTableDynRels.insert(std::make_pair((uint64_t)Rela.r_offset, Rela));
2696 }
2697 } else {
2698 for (const Elf_Rel &Rel : RelRegion.getAsArrayRef<Elf_Rel>()) {
2699 if (Rel.r_offset >= CapTableStartVaddr &&
2700 Rel.r_offset < CapTableEndVaddr) {
2701 Elf_Rela Rela;
2702 Rela.r_offset = Rel.r_offset;
2703 Rela.r_info = Rel.r_info;
2704 Rela.r_addend = 0;
2705 CapTableDynRels.insert(std::make_pair((uint64_t)Rela.r_offset, Rela));
2706 }
2707 }
2708 }
2709 };
2710 FindRelocs(getDynPLTRelRegion());
2711 FindRelocs(getDynRelRegion());
2712 FindRelocs(getDynRelaRegion());
2713
2714 typename ELFT::SymRange DynSyms = dynamic_symbols();
2715 for (uint64_t Offset = CapTableStartVaddr; Offset < CapTableEndVaddr;
2716 Offset += CapSize) {
2717 // Find name:
2718 const auto &Name = SymbolNames.find(Offset);
2719 formatted_raw_ostream OS(W.startLine());
2720 OS << W.hex(Offset - CapTableStartVaddr);
2721 OS.PadToColumn(9u);
2722 if (Name == SymbolNames.end())
2723 OS << "<unknown symbol>"
2724 << " ";
2725 else
2726 OS << Name->second << " ";
2727
2728 auto Reloc = CapTableDynRels.find(Offset);
2729 if (Reloc != CapTableDynRels.end()) {
2730 OS.PadToColumn(40u);
2731 auto R = Reloc->second;
2732 SmallString<32> RelocName;
2733 StringRef TargetName;
2734 Obj->getRelocationTypeName(R.getType(Obj->isMips64EL()), RelocName);
2735 uint32_t SymIndex = R.getSymbol(Obj->isMips64EL());
2736
2737 const Elf_Sym *Sym = unwrapOrError(getSymbol<ELFT>(DynSyms, SymIndex));
2738 if (Sym) {
2739 TargetName = unwrapOrError(Sym->getName(getDynamicStringTable()));
2740 }
2741 OS << " " << RelocName << " against " << TargetName;
2742 // TODO: getSymbol(dynamic_symbols()); StrTable = DynamicStringTable;
2743 }
2744 OS << "\n";
2745 }
2746}
2747
2748template <class ELFT> void ELFDumper<ELFT>::printCheriCapTableMapping() {
2749 const ELFFile<ELFT> *Obj = ObjF->getELFFile();
2750 const Elf_Shdr *Shdr = findSectionByName(*Obj, ".captable_mapping");
2751 if (!Shdr) {
2752 W.startLine() << "There is no .captable_mapping section in the file.\n";
2753 return;
2754 }
2755 ArrayRef<uint8_t> Data = unwrapOrError(Obj->getSectionContents(Shdr));
2756 const size_t EntrySize = 24;
2757
2758 typename ELFT::SymRange Syms;
2759 StringRef StrTable;
2760 bool UsingDynsym = false;
2761 if (DotSymtabSec) {
2762 StrTable = unwrapOrError(Obj->getStringTableForSymtab(*DotSymtabSec));
2763 Syms = unwrapOrError(Obj->symbols(DotSymtabSec));
2764 } else {
2765 StrTable = DynamicStringTable;
2766 Syms = dynamic_symbols();
2767 UsingDynsym = true;
2768 }
2769
2770 ListScope L(W, "CHERI .captable per-file/per-function mapping information");
2771 for (int CurrentOffset = 0, e = Data.size(); CurrentOffset < e;
2772 CurrentOffset += EntrySize) {
2773 const uint8_t *CurrentEntry = Data.data() + CurrentOffset;
2774 uint64_t FunctionStart =
2775 support::endian::read64<ELFT::TargetEndianness>(CurrentEntry);
2776 uint64_t FunctionEnd =
2777 support::endian::read64<ELFT::TargetEndianness>(CurrentEntry + 8);
2778 uint32_t TableOffset =
2779 support::endian::read32<ELFT::TargetEndianness>(CurrentEntry + 16);
2780 uint32_t SubTableLength =
2781 support::endian::read32<ELFT::TargetEndianness>(CurrentEntry + 20);
2782 auto& OS = W.startLine();
2783 OS << "Function start: " << W.hex(FunctionStart);
2784 // Try to find a matching symbol
2785 std::string SymName = "<unknown function>";
2786 for (const auto &Sym : Syms) {
2787 if (Sym.getType() != ELF::STT_FUNC)
2788 continue;
2789 if (Sym.st_value >= FunctionStart && Sym.st_value < FunctionEnd) {
2790 SymName = getFullSymbolName(&Sym, StrTable, UsingDynsym);
2791 break;
2792 }
2793 }
2794 OS << " (" << SymName << ")";
2795 OS << " Function end: " << W.hex(FunctionEnd)
2796 << " .captable offset: " << W.hex(TableOffset)
2797 << " Length:" << W.hex(SubTableLength) << "\n";
2798 }
2799}

2830template <class ELFT> void ELFDumper<ELFT>::printMipsOptions() {

2835 return;
2836 }
2837

2839

2851 break;
2852 default:
2853 W.startLine() << "Unsupported MIPS options tag.\n";
2854 break;
2855 }
2856 Sec = Sec.slice(O->size);
2857 }

2898template <class ELFT>
2899static std::string getSectionHeadersNumString(const ELFFile<ELFT> *Obj) {
2900 const typename ELFT::Ehdr *ElfHeader = Obj->getHeader();
2901 if (ElfHeader->e_shnum != 0)
2902 return to_string(ElfHeader->e_shnum);
2903
2904 ArrayRef<typename ELFT::Shdr> Arr = unwrapOrError(Obj->sections());
2905 if (Arr.empty())
2906 return "0";
2907 return "0 (" + to_string(Arr[0].sh_size) + ")";
2908}
2909
2910template <class ELFT>
2911static std::string getSectionHeaderTableIndexString(const ELFFile<ELFT> *Obj) {
2912 const typename ELFT::Ehdr *ElfHeader = Obj->getHeader();
2913 if (ElfHeader->e_shstrndx != SHN_XINDEX)
2914 return to_string(ElfHeader->e_shstrndx);
2915
2916 ArrayRef<typename ELFT::Shdr> Arr = unwrapOrError(Obj->sections());
2917 if (Arr.empty())
2918 return "65535 (corrupt: out of range)";
2919 return to_string(ElfHeader->e_shstrndx) + " (" + to_string(Arr[0].sh_link) +
2920 ")";
2921}

2923template <class ELFT> void GNUStyle<ELFT>::printFileHeaders(const ELFO *Obj) {
2924 const Elf_Ehdr *e = Obj->getHeader();
2925 OS << "ELF Header:\n";
2926 OS << " Magic: ";
2927 std::string Str;
2928 for (int i = 0; i < ELF::EI_NIDENT; i++)
2929 OS << format(" %02x", static_cast<int>(e->e_ident[i]));
2930 OS << "\n";
2931 Str = printEnum(e->e_ident[ELF::EI_CLASS], makeArrayRef(ElfClass));
2932 printFields(OS, "Class:", Str);
2933 Str = printEnum(e->e_ident[ELF::EI_DATA], makeArrayRef(ElfDataEncoding));
2934 printFields(OS, "Data:", Str);
2935 OS.PadToColumn(2u);
2936 OS << "Version:";
2937 OS.PadToColumn(37u);
2938 OS << to_hexString(e->e_ident[ELF::EI_VERSION]);
2939 if (e->e_version == ELF::EV_CURRENT)
2940 OS << " (current)";
2941 OS << "\n";
2942 Str = printEnum(e->e_ident[ELF::EI_OSABI], makeArrayRef(ElfOSABI));
2943 printFields(OS, "OS/ABI:", Str);
2944 Str = "0x" + to_hexString(e->e_ident[ELF::EI_ABIVERSION]);
2945 printFields(OS, "ABI Version:", Str);
2946 Str = printEnum(e->e_type, makeArrayRef(ElfObjectFileType));
2947 printFields(OS, "Type:", Str);
2948 Str = printEnum(e->e_machine, makeArrayRef(ElfMachineType));
2949 printFields(OS, "Machine:", Str);
2950 Str = "0x" + to_hexString(e->e_version);
2951 printFields(OS, "Version:", Str);
2952 Str = "0x" + to_hexString(e->e_entry);
2953 printFields(OS, "Entry point address:", Str);
2954 Str = to_string(e->e_phoff) + " (bytes into file)";
2955 printFields(OS, "Start of program headers:", Str);
2956 Str = to_string(e->e_shoff) + " (bytes into file)";
2957 printFields(OS, "Start of section headers:", Str);
2958 std::string ElfFlags;
2959 if (e->e_machine == EM_MIPS)
2960 ElfFlags =
2961 printFlags(e->e_flags, makeArrayRef(ElfHeaderMipsFlags),
2962 unsigned(ELF::EF_MIPS_ARCH), unsigned(ELF::EF_MIPS_ABI),
2963 unsigned(ELF::EF_MIPS_MACH));
2964 else if (e->e_machine == EM_RISCV)
2965 ElfFlags = printFlags(e->e_flags, makeArrayRef(ElfHeaderRISCVFlags));
2966 Str = "0x" + to_hexString(e->e_flags);
2967 if (!ElfFlags.empty())
2968 Str = Str + ", " + ElfFlags;
2969 printFields(OS, "Flags:", Str);
2970 Str = to_string(e->e_ehsize) + " (bytes)";
2971 printFields(OS, "Size of this header:", Str);
2972 Str = to_string(e->e_phentsize) + " (bytes)";
2973 printFields(OS, "Size of program headers:", Str);
2974 Str = to_string(e->e_phnum);
2975 printFields(OS, "Number of program headers:", Str);
2976 Str = to_string(e->e_shentsize) + " (bytes)";
2977 printFields(OS, "Size of section headers:", Str);
2978 Str = getSectionHeadersNumString(Obj);
2979 printFields(OS, "Number of section headers:", Str);
2980 Str = getSectionHeaderTableIndexString(Obj);
2981 printFields(OS, "Section header string table index:", Str);
2982}

2984namespace {
2985struct GroupMember {
2986 StringRef Name;
2987 uint64_t Index;
2988};
2989
2990struct GroupSection {
2991 StringRef Name;
2992 std::string Signature;
2993 uint64_t ShName;
2994 uint64_t Index;
2995 uint32_t Link;
2996 uint32_t Info;
2997 uint32_t Type;
2998 std::vector<GroupMember> Members;
2999};
3000
3001template <class ELFT>
3002std::vector<GroupSection> getGroups(const ELFFile<ELFT> *Obj) {
3003 using Elf_Shdr = typename ELFT::Shdr;
3004 using Elf_Sym = typename ELFT::Sym;
3005 using Elf_Word = typename ELFT::Word;
3006
3007 std::vector<GroupSection> Ret;
3008 uint64_t I = 0;
3009 for (const Elf_Shdr &Sec : unwrapOrError(Obj->sections())) {
3010 ++I;
3011 if (Sec.sh_type != ELF::SHT_GROUP)
3012 continue;
3013
3014 const Elf_Shdr *Symtab = unwrapOrError(Obj->getSection(Sec.sh_link));
3015 StringRef StrTable = unwrapOrError(Obj->getStringTableForSymtab(*Symtab));
3016 const Elf_Sym *Sym =
3017 unwrapOrError(Obj->template getEntry<Elf_Sym>(Symtab, Sec.sh_info));
3018 auto Data =
3019 unwrapOrError(Obj->template getSectionContentsAsArray<Elf_Word>(&Sec));
3020
3021 StringRef Name = unwrapOrError(Obj->getSectionName(&Sec));
3022 StringRef Signature = StrTable.data() + Sym->st_name;
3023 Ret.push_back({Name,
3024 maybeDemangle(Signature),
3025 Sec.sh_name,
3026 I - 1,
3027 Sec.sh_link,
3028 Sec.sh_info,
3029 Data[0],
3030 {}});
3031
3032 std::vector<GroupMember> &GM = Ret.back().Members;
3033 for (uint32_t Ndx : Data.slice(1)) {
3034 auto Sec = unwrapOrError(Obj->getSection(Ndx));
3035 const StringRef Name = unwrapOrError(Obj->getSectionName(Sec));
3036 GM.push_back({Name, Ndx});
3037 }
3038 }
3039 return Ret;
3040}
3041
3042DenseMap<uint64_t, const GroupSection *>
3043mapSectionsToGroups(ArrayRef<GroupSection> Groups) {
3044 DenseMap<uint64_t, const GroupSection *> Ret;
3045 for (const GroupSection &G : Groups)
3046 for (const GroupMember &GM : G.Members)
3047 Ret.insert({GM.Index, &G});
3048 return Ret;
3049}
3050
3051} // namespace

3053template <class ELFT> void GNUStyle<ELFT>::printGroupSections(const ELFO *Obj) {
3054 std::vector<GroupSection> V = getGroups<ELFT>(Obj);
3055 DenseMap<uint64_t, const GroupSection *> Map = mapSectionsToGroups(V);
3056 for (const GroupSection &G : V) {
3057 OS << "\n"
3058 << getGroupType(G.Type) << " group section ["
3059 << format_decimal(G.Index, 5) << "] `" << G.Name << "' [" << G.Signature
3060 << "] contains " << G.Members.size() << " sections:\n"
3061 << " [Index] Name\n";
3062 for (const GroupMember &GM : G.Members) {
3063 const GroupSection *MainGroup = Map[GM.Index];
3064 if (MainGroup != &G) {
3065 OS.flush();
3066 errs() << "Error: section [" << format_decimal(GM.Index, 5)
3067 << "] in group section [" << format_decimal(G.Index, 5)
3068 << "] already in group section ["
3069 << format_decimal(MainGroup->Index, 5) << "]";
3070 errs().flush();
3071 continue;
3072 }
3073 OS << " [" << format_decimal(GM.Index, 5) << "] " << GM.Name << "\n";
3074 }
3075 }
3076
3077 if (V.empty())
3078 OS << "There are no section groups in this file.\n";
3079}

3081template <class ELFT>
3082void GNUStyle<ELFT>::printRelocation(const ELFO *Obj, const Elf_Shdr *SymTab,
3083 const Elf_Rela &R, bool IsRela) {
3084 const Elf_Sym *Sym = unwrapOrError(Obj->getRelocationSymbol(&R, SymTab));
3085 std::string TargetName;
3086 if (Sym && Sym->getType() == ELF::STT_SECTION) {
3087 const Elf_Shdr *Sec = unwrapOrError(
3088 Obj->getSection(Sym, SymTab, this->dumper()->getShndxTable()));
3089 TargetName = unwrapOrError(Obj->getSectionName(Sec));
3090 } else if (Sym) {
3091 StringRef StrTable = unwrapOrError(Obj->getStringTableForSymtab(*SymTab));
3092 TargetName = this->dumper()->getFullSymbolName(
3093 Sym, StrTable, SymTab->sh_type == SHT_DYNSYM /* IsDynamic */);
3094 }
3095 printRelocation(Obj, Sym, TargetName, R, IsRela);
3096}
3097
3098template <class ELFT>
3099void GNUStyle<ELFT>::printRelocation(const ELFO *Obj, const Elf_Sym *Sym,
3100 StringRef SymbolName, const Elf_Rela &R,
3101 bool IsRela) {
3102 // First two fields are bit width dependent. The rest of them are fixed width.
3103 unsigned Bias = ELFT::Is64Bits ? 8 : 0;
3104 Field Fields[5] = {0, 10 + Bias, 19 + 2 * Bias, 42 + 2 * Bias, 53 + 2 * Bias};
3105 unsigned Width = ELFT::Is64Bits ? 16 : 8;
3106
3107 Fields[0].Str = to_string(format_hex_no_prefix(R.r_offset, Width));
3108 Fields[1].Str = to_string(format_hex_no_prefix(R.r_info, Width));
3109
3110 SmallString<32> RelocName;
3111 Obj->getRelocationTypeName(R.getType(Obj->isMips64EL()), RelocName);
3112 Fields[2].Str = RelocName.c_str();
3113
3114 if (Sym && (!SymbolName.empty() || Sym->getValue() != 0))
3115 Fields[3].Str = to_string(format_hex_no_prefix(Sym->getValue(), Width));
3116
3117 Fields[4].Str = SymbolName;
3118 for (const Field &F : Fields)
3119 printField(F);
3120
3121 std::string Addend;
3122 if (IsRela) {
3123 int64_t RelAddend = R.r_addend;
3124 if (!SymbolName.empty()) {
3125 if (R.r_addend < 0) {
3126 Addend = " - ";
3127 RelAddend = std::abs(RelAddend);
3128 } else
3129 Addend = " + ";
3130 }
3131
3132 Addend += to_hexString(RelAddend, false);
3133 }
3134 OS << Addend << "\n";
3135}

3137template <class ELFT> void GNUStyle<ELFT>::printRelocHeader(unsigned SType) {
3138 bool IsRela = SType == ELF::SHT_RELA || SType == ELF::SHT_ANDROID_RELA;
3139 bool IsRelr = SType == ELF::SHT_RELR || SType == ELF::SHT_ANDROID_RELR;
3140 if (ELFT::Is64Bits)
3141 OS << " ";
3142 else
3143 OS << " ";
3144 if (IsRelr && opts::RawRelr)
3145 OS << "Data ";
3146 else
3147 OS << "Offset";
3148 if (ELFT::Is64Bits)
3149 OS << " Info Type"
3150 << " Symbol's Value Symbol's Name";
3151 else
3152 OS << " Info Type Sym. Value Symbol's Name";
3153 if (IsRela)
3154 OS << " + Addend";
3155 OS << "\n";
3156}
3157
3158template <class ELFT> void GNUStyle<ELFT>::printRelocations(const ELFO *Obj) {
3159 bool HasRelocSections = false;
3160 for (const Elf_Shdr &Sec : unwrapOrError(Obj->sections())) {
3161 if (Sec.sh_type != ELF::SHT_REL && Sec.sh_type != ELF::SHT_RELA &&
3162 Sec.sh_type != ELF::SHT_RELR && Sec.sh_type != ELF::SHT_ANDROID_REL &&
3163 Sec.sh_type != ELF::SHT_ANDROID_RELA &&
3164 Sec.sh_type != ELF::SHT_ANDROID_RELR)
3165 continue;
3166 HasRelocSections = true;
3167 StringRef Name = unwrapOrError(Obj->getSectionName(&Sec));
3168 unsigned Entries = Sec.getEntityCount();
3169 std::vector<Elf_Rela> AndroidRelas;
3170 if (Sec.sh_type == ELF::SHT_ANDROID_REL ||
3171 Sec.sh_type == ELF::SHT_ANDROID_RELA) {
3172 // Android's packed relocation section needs to be unpacked first
3173 // to get the actual number of entries.
3174 AndroidRelas = unwrapOrError(Obj->android_relas(&Sec));
3175 Entries = AndroidRelas.size();
3176 }
3177 std::vector<Elf_Rela> RelrRelas;
3178 if (!opts::RawRelr && (Sec.sh_type == ELF::SHT_RELR ||
3179 Sec.sh_type == ELF::SHT_ANDROID_RELR)) {
3180 // .relr.dyn relative relocation section needs to be unpacked first
3181 // to get the actual number of entries.
3182 Elf_Relr_Range Relrs = unwrapOrError(Obj->relrs(&Sec));
3183 RelrRelas = unwrapOrError(Obj->decode_relrs(Relrs));
3184 Entries = RelrRelas.size();
3185 }
3186 uintX_t Offset = Sec.sh_offset;
3187 OS << "\nRelocation section '" << Name << "' at offset 0x"
3188 << to_hexString(Offset, false) << " contains " << Entries
3189 << " entries:\n";
3190 printRelocHeader(Sec.sh_type);
3191 const Elf_Shdr *SymTab = unwrapOrError(Obj->getSection(Sec.sh_link));
3192 switch (Sec.sh_type) {
3193 case ELF::SHT_REL:
3194 for (const auto &R : unwrapOrError(Obj->rels(&Sec))) {
3195 Elf_Rela Rela;
3196 Rela.r_offset = R.r_offset;
3197 Rela.r_info = R.r_info;
3198 Rela.r_addend = 0; // FIXME: this is wrong....
3199 printRelocation(Obj, SymTab, Rela, false);
3200 }
3201 break;
3202 case ELF::SHT_RELA:
3203 for (const auto &R : unwrapOrError(Obj->relas(&Sec)))
3204 printRelocation(Obj, SymTab, R, true);
3205 break;
3206 case ELF::SHT_RELR:
3207 case ELF::SHT_ANDROID_RELR:
3208 if (opts::RawRelr)
3209 for (const auto &R : unwrapOrError(Obj->relrs(&Sec)))
3210 OS << to_string(format_hex_no_prefix(R, ELFT::Is64Bits ? 16 : 8))
3211 << "\n";
3212 else
3213 for (const auto &R : RelrRelas)
3214 printRelocation(Obj, SymTab, R, false);
3215 break;
3216 case ELF::SHT_ANDROID_REL:
3217 case ELF::SHT_ANDROID_RELA:
3218 for (const auto &R : AndroidRelas)
3219 printRelocation(Obj, SymTab, R, Sec.sh_type == ELF::SHT_ANDROID_RELA);
3220 break;
3221 }
3222 }
3223 if (!HasRelocSections)
3224 OS << "\nThere are no relocations in this file.\n";
3225}
3226
3227// Print the offset of a particular section from anyone of the ranges:
3228// [SHT_LOOS, SHT_HIOS], [SHT_LOPROC, SHT_HIPROC], [SHT_LOUSER, SHT_HIUSER].
3229// If 'Type' does not fall within any of those ranges, then a string is
3230// returned as '<unknown>' followed by the type value.
3231static std::string getSectionTypeOffsetString(unsigned Type) {
3232 if (Type >= SHT_LOOS && Type <= SHT_HIOS)
3233 return "LOOS+0x" + to_hexString(Type - SHT_LOOS);
3234 else if (Type >= SHT_LOPROC && Type <= SHT_HIPROC)
3235 return "LOPROC+0x" + to_hexString(Type - SHT_LOPROC);
3236 else if (Type >= SHT_LOUSER && Type <= SHT_HIUSER)
3237 return "LOUSER+0x" + to_hexString(Type - SHT_LOUSER);
3238 return "0x" + to_hexString(Type) + ": <unknown>";
3239}
3240
3241static std::string getSectionTypeString(unsigned Arch, unsigned Type) {
3242 using namespace ELF;
3243
3244 switch (Arch) {
3245 case EM_ARM:
3246 switch (Type) {
3247 case SHT_ARM_EXIDX:
3248 return "ARM_EXIDX";
3249 case SHT_ARM_PREEMPTMAP:
3250 return "ARM_PREEMPTMAP";
3251 case SHT_ARM_ATTRIBUTES:
3252 return "ARM_ATTRIBUTES";
3253 case SHT_ARM_DEBUGOVERLAY:
3254 return "ARM_DEBUGOVERLAY";
3255 case SHT_ARM_OVERLAYSECTION:
3256 return "ARM_OVERLAYSECTION";
3257 }
3258 break;
3259 case EM_X86_64:
3260 switch (Type) {
3261 case SHT_X86_64_UNWIND:
3262 return "X86_64_UNWIND";
3263 }
3264 break;
3265 case EM_MIPS:
3266 case EM_MIPS_RS3_LE:
3267 switch (Type) {
3268 case SHT_MIPS_REGINFO:
3269 return "MIPS_REGINFO";
3270 case SHT_MIPS_OPTIONS:
3271 return "MIPS_OPTIONS";
3272 case SHT_MIPS_DWARF:
3273 return "MIPS_DWARF";
3274 case SHT_MIPS_ABIFLAGS:
3275 return "MIPS_ABIFLAGS";
3276 }
3277 break;
3278 }
3279 switch (Type) {
3280 case SHT_NULL:
3281 return "NULL";
3282 case SHT_PROGBITS:
3283 return "PROGBITS";
3284 case SHT_SYMTAB:
3285 return "SYMTAB";
3286 case SHT_STRTAB:
3287 return "STRTAB";
3288 case SHT_RELA:
3289 return "RELA";
3290 case SHT_HASH:
3291 return "HASH";
3292 case SHT_DYNAMIC:
3293 return "DYNAMIC";
3294 case SHT_NOTE:
3295 return "NOTE";
3296 case SHT_NOBITS:
3297 return "NOBITS";
3298 case SHT_REL:
3299 return "REL";
3300 case SHT_SHLIB:
3301 return "SHLIB";
3302 case SHT_DYNSYM:
3303 return "DYNSYM";
3304 case SHT_INIT_ARRAY:
3305 return "INIT_ARRAY";
3306 case SHT_FINI_ARRAY:
3307 return "FINI_ARRAY";
3308 case SHT_PREINIT_ARRAY:
3309 return "PREINIT_ARRAY";
3310 case SHT_GROUP:
3311 return "GROUP";
3312 case SHT_SYMTAB_SHNDX:
3313 return "SYMTAB SECTION INDICES";
3314 case SHT_ANDROID_REL:
3315 return "ANDROID_REL";
3316 case SHT_ANDROID_RELA:
3317 return "ANDROID_RELA";
3318 case SHT_RELR:
3319 case SHT_ANDROID_RELR:
3320 return "RELR";
3321 case SHT_LLVM_ODRTAB:
3322 return "LLVM_ODRTAB";
3323 case SHT_LLVM_LINKER_OPTIONS:
3324 return "LLVM_LINKER_OPTIONS";
3325 case SHT_LLVM_CALL_GRAPH_PROFILE:
3326 return "LLVM_CALL_GRAPH_PROFILE";
3327 case SHT_LLVM_ADDRSIG:
3328 return "LLVM_ADDRSIG";
3329 case SHT_LLVM_DEPENDENT_LIBRARIES:
3330 return "LLVM_DEPENDENT_LIBRARIES";
3331 // FIXME: Parse processor specific GNU attributes
3332 case SHT_GNU_ATTRIBUTES:
3333 return "ATTRIBUTES";
3334 case SHT_GNU_HASH:
3335 return "GNU_HASH";
3336 case SHT_GNU_verdef:
3337 return "VERDEF";
3338 case SHT_GNU_verneed:
3339 return "VERNEED";
3340 case SHT_GNU_versym:
3341 return "VERSYM";
3342 default:
3343 return getSectionTypeOffsetString(Type);
3344 }
3345 return "";
3346}

3348template <class ELFT>
3349void GNUStyle<ELFT>::printSectionHeaders(const ELFO *Obj) {
3350 unsigned Bias = ELFT::Is64Bits ? 0 : 8;
3351 ArrayRef<Elf_Shdr> Sections = unwrapOrError(Obj->sections());
3352 OS << "There are " << to_string(Sections.size())
3353 << " section headers, starting at offset "
3354 << "0x" << to_hexString(Obj->getHeader()->e_shoff, false) << ":\n\n";
3355 OS << "Section Headers:\n";
3356 Field Fields[11] = {
3357 {"[Nr]", 2}, {"Name", 7}, {"Type", 25},
3358 {"Address", 41}, {"Off", 58 - Bias}, {"Size", 65 - Bias},
3359 {"ES", 72 - Bias}, {"Flg", 75 - Bias}, {"Lk", 79 - Bias},
3360 {"Inf", 82 - Bias}, {"Al", 86 - Bias}};
3361 for (auto &F : Fields)
3362 printField(F);
3363 OS << "\n";
3364
3365 size_t SectionIndex = 0;
3366 for (const Elf_Shdr &Sec : Sections) {
3367 Fields[0].Str = to_string(SectionIndex);
3368 Fields[1].Str = unwrapOrError(Obj->getSectionName(&Sec));
3369 Fields[2].Str =
3370 getSectionTypeString(Obj->getHeader()->e_machine, Sec.sh_type);
3371 Fields[3].Str =
3372 to_string(format_hex_no_prefix(Sec.sh_addr, ELFT::Is64Bits ? 16 : 8));
3373 Fields[4].Str = to_string(format_hex_no_prefix(Sec.sh_offset, 6));
3374 Fields[5].Str = to_string(format_hex_no_prefix(Sec.sh_size, 6));
3375 Fields[6].Str = to_string(format_hex_no_prefix(Sec.sh_entsize, 2));
3376 Fields[7].Str = getGNUFlags(Sec.sh_flags);
3377 Fields[8].Str = to_string(Sec.sh_link);
3378 Fields[9].Str = to_string(Sec.sh_info);
3379 Fields[10].Str = to_string(Sec.sh_addralign);
3380
3381 OS.PadToColumn(Fields[0].Column);
3382 OS << "[" << right_justify(Fields[0].Str, 2) << "]";
3383 for (int i = 1; i < 7; i++)
3384 printField(Fields[i]);
3385 OS.PadToColumn(Fields[7].Column);
3386 OS << right_justify(Fields[7].Str, 3);
3387 OS.PadToColumn(Fields[8].Column);
3388 OS << right_justify(Fields[8].Str, 2);
3389 OS.PadToColumn(Fields[9].Column);
3390 OS << right_justify(Fields[9].Str, 3);
3391 OS.PadToColumn(Fields[10].Column);
3392 OS << right_justify(Fields[10].Str, 2);
3393 OS << "\n";
3394 ++SectionIndex;
3395 }
3396 OS << "Key to Flags:\n"
3397 << " W (write), A (alloc), X (execute), M (merge), S (strings), l "
3398 "(large)\n"
3399 << " I (info), L (link order), G (group), T (TLS), E (exclude),\
3400 x (unknown)\n"
3401 << " O (extra OS processing required) o (OS specific),\
3402 p (processor specific)\n";
3403}
