3405template <class ELFT>
3406void GNUStyle<ELFT>::printSymtabMessage(const ELFO *Obj, StringRef Name,
3407 size_t Entries) {
3408 if (!Name.empty())
3409 OS << "\nSymbol table '" << Name << "' contains " << Entries
3410 << " entries:\n";
3411 else
3412 OS << "\n Symbol table for image:\n";
3413
3414 if (ELFT::Is64Bits)
3415 OS << " Num: Value Size Type Bind Vis Ndx Name\n";
3416 else
3417 OS << " Num: Value Size Type Bind Vis Ndx Name\n";
3418}
3419
3420template <class ELFT>
3421std::string GNUStyle<ELFT>::getSymbolSectionNdx(const ELFO *Obj,
3422 const Elf_Sym *Symbol,
3423 const Elf_Sym *FirstSym) {
3424 unsigned SectionIndex = Symbol->st_shndx;
3425 switch (SectionIndex) {
3426 case ELF::SHN_UNDEF:
3427 return "UND";
3428 case ELF::SHN_ABS:
3429 return "ABS";
3430 case ELF::SHN_COMMON:
3431 return "COM";
3432 case ELF::SHN_XINDEX:
3433 return to_string(
3434 format_decimal(unwrapOrError(object::getExtendedSymbolTableIndex<ELFT>(
3435 Symbol, FirstSym, this->dumper()->getShndxTable())),
3436 3));
3437 default:
3438 // Find if:
3439 // Processor specific
3440 if (SectionIndex >= ELF::SHN_LOPROC && SectionIndex <= ELF::SHN_HIPROC)
3441 return std::string("PRC[0x") +
3442 to_string(format_hex_no_prefix(SectionIndex, 4)) + "]";
3443 // OS specific
3444 if (SectionIndex >= ELF::SHN_LOOS && SectionIndex <= ELF::SHN_HIOS)
3445 return std::string("OS[0x") +
3446 to_string(format_hex_no_prefix(SectionIndex, 4)) + "]";
3447 // Architecture reserved:
3448 if (SectionIndex >= ELF::SHN_LORESERVE &&
3449 SectionIndex <= ELF::SHN_HIRESERVE)
3450 return std::string("RSV[0x") +
3451 to_string(format_hex_no_prefix(SectionIndex, 4)) + "]";
3452 // A normal section with an index
3453 return to_string(format_decimal(SectionIndex, 3));
3454 }
3455}
3456
3457template <class ELFT>
3458void GNUStyle<ELFT>::printSymbol(const ELFO *Obj, const Elf_Sym *Symbol,
3459 const Elf_Sym *FirstSym, StringRef StrTable,
3460 bool IsDynamic) {
3461 static int Idx = 0;
3462 static bool Dynamic = true;
3463
3464 // If this function was called with a different value from IsDynamic
3465 // from last call, happens when we move from dynamic to static symbol
3466 // table, "Num" field should be reset.
3467 if (!Dynamic != !IsDynamic) {
3468 Idx = 0;
3469 Dynamic = false;
3470 }
3471
3472 unsigned Bias = ELFT::Is64Bits ? 8 : 0;
3473 Field Fields[8] = {0, 8, 17 + Bias, 23 + Bias,
3474 31 + Bias, 38 + Bias, 47 + Bias, 51 + Bias};
3475 Fields[0].Str = to_string(format_decimal(Idx++, 6)) + ":";
3476 Fields[1].Str = to_string(
3477 format_hex_no_prefix(Symbol->st_value, ELFT::Is64Bits ? 16 : 8));
3478 Fields[2].Str = to_string(format_decimal(Symbol->st_size, 5));
3479
3480 unsigned char SymbolType = Symbol->getType();
3481 if (Obj->getHeader()->e_machine == ELF::EM_AMDGPU &&
3482 SymbolType >= ELF::STT_LOOS && SymbolType < ELF::STT_HIOS)
3483 Fields[3].Str = printEnum(SymbolType, makeArrayRef(AMDGPUSymbolTypes));
3484 else
3485 Fields[3].Str = printEnum(SymbolType, makeArrayRef(ElfSymbolTypes));
3486
3487 Fields[4].Str =
3488 printEnum(Symbol->getBinding(), makeArrayRef(ElfSymbolBindings));
3489 Fields[5].Str =
3490 printEnum(Symbol->getVisibility(), makeArrayRef(ElfSymbolVisibilities));
3491 Fields[6].Str = getSymbolSectionNdx(Obj, Symbol, FirstSym);
3492 Fields[7].Str =
3493 this->dumper()->getFullSymbolName(Symbol, StrTable, IsDynamic);
3494 for (auto &Entry : Fields)
3495 printField(Entry);
3496 OS << "\n";
3497}
3498
3499template <class ELFT>
3500void GNUStyle<ELFT>::printHashedSymbol(const ELFO *Obj, const Elf_Sym *FirstSym,
3501 uint32_t Sym, StringRef StrTable,
3502 uint32_t Bucket) {
3503 unsigned Bias = ELFT::Is64Bits ? 8 : 0;
3504 Field Fields[9] = {0, 6, 11, 20 + Bias, 25 + Bias,
3505 34 + Bias, 41 + Bias, 49 + Bias, 53 + Bias};
3506 Fields[0].Str = to_string(format_decimal(Sym, 5));
3507 Fields[1].Str = to_string(format_decimal(Bucket, 3)) + ":";
3508
3509 const auto Symbol = FirstSym + Sym;
3510 Fields[2].Str = to_string(
3511 format_hex_no_prefix(Symbol->st_value, ELFT::Is64Bits ? 18 : 8));
3512 Fields[3].Str = to_string(format_decimal(Symbol->st_size, 5));
3513
3514 unsigned char SymbolType = Symbol->getType();
3515 if (Obj->getHeader()->e_machine == ELF::EM_AMDGPU &&
3516 SymbolType >= ELF::STT_LOOS && SymbolType < ELF::STT_HIOS)
3517 Fields[4].Str = printEnum(SymbolType, makeArrayRef(AMDGPUSymbolTypes));
3518 else
3519 Fields[4].Str = printEnum(SymbolType, makeArrayRef(ElfSymbolTypes));
3520
3521 Fields[5].Str =
3522 printEnum(Symbol->getBinding(), makeArrayRef(ElfSymbolBindings));
3523 Fields[6].Str =
3524 printEnum(Symbol->getVisibility(), makeArrayRef(ElfSymbolVisibilities));
3525 Fields[7].Str = getSymbolSectionNdx(Obj, Symbol, FirstSym);
3526 Fields[8].Str = this->dumper()->getFullSymbolName(Symbol, StrTable, true);
3527
3528 for (auto &Entry : Fields)
3529 printField(Entry);
3530 OS << "\n";
3531}
3532
3533template <class ELFT>
3534void GNUStyle<ELFT>::printSymbols(const ELFO *Obj, bool PrintSymbols,
3535 bool PrintDynamicSymbols) {
3536 if (!PrintSymbols && !PrintDynamicSymbols)
3537 return;
3538 // GNU readelf prints both the .dynsym and .symtab with --symbols.
3539 this->dumper()->printSymbolsHelper(true);
3540 if (PrintSymbols)
3541 this->dumper()->printSymbolsHelper(false);
3542}
3543
3544template <class ELFT> void GNUStyle<ELFT>::printHashSymbols(const ELFO *Obj) {
3545 if (this->dumper()->getDynamicStringTable().empty())
3546 return;
3547 auto StringTable = this->dumper()->getDynamicStringTable();
3548 auto DynSyms = this->dumper()->dynamic_symbols();
3549
3550 // Try printing .hash
3551 if (auto SysVHash = this->dumper()->getHashTable()) {
3552 OS << "\n Symbol table of .hash for image:\n";
3553 if (ELFT::Is64Bits)
3554 OS << " Num Buc: Value Size Type Bind Vis Ndx Name";
3555 else
3556 OS << " Num Buc: Value Size Type Bind Vis Ndx Name";
3557 OS << "\n";
3558
3559 auto Buckets = SysVHash->buckets();
3560 auto Chains = SysVHash->chains();
3561 for (uint32_t Buc = 0; Buc < SysVHash->nbucket; Buc++) {
3562 if (Buckets[Buc] == ELF::STN_UNDEF)
3563 continue;
3564 for (uint32_t Ch = Buckets[Buc]; Ch < SysVHash->nchain; Ch = Chains[Ch]) {
3565 if (Ch == ELF::STN_UNDEF)
3566 break;
3567 printHashedSymbol(Obj, &DynSyms[0], Ch, StringTable, Buc);
3568 }
3569 }
3570 }
3571
3572 // Try printing .gnu.hash
3573 if (auto GnuHash = this->dumper()->getGnuHashTable()) {
3574 OS << "\n Symbol table of .gnu.hash for image:\n";
3575 if (ELFT::Is64Bits)
3576 OS << " Num Buc: Value Size Type Bind Vis Ndx Name";
3577 else
3578 OS << " Num Buc: Value Size Type Bind Vis Ndx Name";
3579 OS << "\n";
3580 auto Buckets = GnuHash->buckets();
3581 for (uint32_t Buc = 0; Buc < GnuHash->nbuckets; Buc++) {
3582 if (Buckets[Buc] == ELF::STN_UNDEF)
3583 continue;
3584 uint32_t Index = Buckets[Buc];
3585 uint32_t GnuHashable = Index - GnuHash->symndx;
3586 // Print whole chain
3587 while (true) {
3588 printHashedSymbol(Obj, &DynSyms[0], Index++, StringTable, Buc);
3589 // Chain ends at symbol with stopper bit
3590 if ((GnuHash->values(DynSyms.size())[GnuHashable++] & 1) == 1)
3591 break;
3592 }
3593 }
3594 }
3595}
3596
3597static inline std::string printPhdrFlags(unsigned Flag) {
3598 std::string Str;
3599 Str = (Flag & PF_R) ? "R" : " ";
3600 Str += (Flag & PF_W) ? "W" : " ";
3601 Str += (Flag & PF_X) ? "E" : " ";
3602 return Str;
3603}
3604
3605// SHF_TLS sections are only in PT_TLS, PT_LOAD or PT_GNU_RELRO
3606// PT_TLS must only have SHF_TLS sections
3607template <class ELFT>
3608bool GNUStyle<ELFT>::checkTLSSections(const Elf_Phdr &Phdr,
3609 const Elf_Shdr &Sec) {
3610 return (((Sec.sh_flags & ELF::SHF_TLS) &&
3611 ((Phdr.p_type == ELF::PT_TLS) || (Phdr.p_type == ELF::PT_LOAD) ||
3612 (Phdr.p_type == ELF::PT_GNU_RELRO))) ||
3613 (!(Sec.sh_flags & ELF::SHF_TLS) && Phdr.p_type != ELF::PT_TLS));
3614}
3615
3616// Non-SHT_NOBITS must have its offset inside the segment
3617// Only non-zero section can be at end of segment
3618template <class ELFT>
3619bool GNUStyle<ELFT>::checkoffsets(const Elf_Phdr &Phdr, const Elf_Shdr &Sec) {
3620 if (Sec.sh_type == ELF::SHT_NOBITS)
3621 return true;
3622 bool IsSpecial =
3623 (Sec.sh_type == ELF::SHT_NOBITS) && ((Sec.sh_flags & ELF::SHF_TLS) != 0);
3624 // .tbss is special, it only has memory in PT_TLS and has NOBITS properties
3625 auto SectionSize =
3626 (IsSpecial && Phdr.p_type != ELF::PT_TLS) ? 0 : Sec.sh_size;
3627 if (Sec.sh_offset >= Phdr.p_offset)
3628 return ((Sec.sh_offset + SectionSize <= Phdr.p_filesz + Phdr.p_offset)
3629 /*only non-zero sized sections at end*/
3630 && (Sec.sh_offset + 1 <= Phdr.p_offset + Phdr.p_filesz));
3631 return false;
3632}
3633
3634// SHF_ALLOC must have VMA inside segment
3635// Only non-zero section can be at end of segment
3636template <class ELFT>
3637bool GNUStyle<ELFT>::checkVMA(const Elf_Phdr &Phdr, const Elf_Shdr &Sec) {
3638 if (!(Sec.sh_flags & ELF::SHF_ALLOC))
3639 return true;
3640 bool IsSpecial =
3641 (Sec.sh_type == ELF::SHT_NOBITS) && ((Sec.sh_flags & ELF::SHF_TLS) != 0);
3642 // .tbss is special, it only has memory in PT_TLS and has NOBITS properties
3643 auto SectionSize =
3644 (IsSpecial && Phdr.p_type != ELF::PT_TLS) ? 0 : Sec.sh_size;
3645 if (Sec.sh_addr >= Phdr.p_vaddr)
3646 return ((Sec.sh_addr + SectionSize <= Phdr.p_vaddr + Phdr.p_memsz) &&
3647 (Sec.sh_addr + 1 <= Phdr.p_vaddr + Phdr.p_memsz));
3648 return false;
3649}
3650
3651// No section with zero size must be at start or end of PT_DYNAMIC
3652template <class ELFT>
3653bool GNUStyle<ELFT>::checkPTDynamic(const Elf_Phdr &Phdr, const Elf_Shdr &Sec) {
3654 if (Phdr.p_type != ELF::PT_DYNAMIC || Sec.sh_size != 0 || Phdr.p_memsz == 0)
3655 return true;
3656 // Is section within the phdr both based on offset and VMA ?
3657 return ((Sec.sh_type == ELF::SHT_NOBITS) ||
3658 (Sec.sh_offset > Phdr.p_offset &&
3659 Sec.sh_offset < Phdr.p_offset + Phdr.p_filesz)) &&
3660 (!(Sec.sh_flags & ELF::SHF_ALLOC) ||
3661 (Sec.sh_addr > Phdr.p_vaddr && Sec.sh_addr < Phdr.p_memsz));
3662}
3663
3664template <class ELFT>
3665void GNUStyle<ELFT>::printProgramHeaders(
3666 const ELFO *Obj, bool PrintProgramHeaders,
3667 cl::boolOrDefault PrintSectionMapping) {
3668 if (PrintProgramHeaders)
3669 printProgramHeaders(Obj);
3670
3671 // Display the section mapping along with the program headers, unless
3672 // -section-mapping is explicitly set to false.
3673 if (PrintSectionMapping != cl::BOU_FALSE)
3674 printSectionMapping(Obj);
3675}
3676
3677template <class ELFT>
3678void GNUStyle<ELFT>::printProgramHeaders(const ELFO *Obj) {
3679 unsigned Bias = ELFT::Is64Bits ? 8 : 0;
3680 const Elf_Ehdr *Header = Obj->getHeader();
3681 Field Fields[8] = {2, 17, 26, 37 + Bias,
3682 48 + Bias, 56 + Bias, 64 + Bias, 68 + Bias};
3683 OS << "\nElf file type is "
3684 << printEnum(Header->e_type, makeArrayRef(ElfObjectFileType)) << "\n"
3685 << "Entry point " << format_hex(Header->e_entry, 3) << "\n"
3686 << "There are " << Header->e_phnum << " program headers,"
3687 << " starting at offset " << Header->e_phoff << "\n\n"
3688 << "Program Headers:\n";
3689 if (ELFT::Is64Bits)
3690 OS << " Type Offset VirtAddr PhysAddr "
3691 << " FileSiz MemSiz Flg Align\n";
3692 else
3693 OS << " Type Offset VirtAddr PhysAddr FileSiz "
3694 << "MemSiz Flg Align\n";
3695
3696 unsigned Width = ELFT::Is64Bits ? 18 : 10;
3697 unsigned SizeWidth = ELFT::Is64Bits ? 8 : 7;
3698 for (const auto &Phdr : unwrapOrError(Obj->program_headers())) {
3699 Fields[0].Str = getElfPtType(Header->e_machine, Phdr.p_type);
3700 Fields[1].Str = to_string(format_hex(Phdr.p_offset, 8));
3701 Fields[2].Str = to_string(format_hex(Phdr.p_vaddr, Width));
3702 Fields[3].Str = to_string(format_hex(Phdr.p_paddr, Width));
3703 Fields[4].Str = to_string(format_hex(Phdr.p_filesz, SizeWidth));
3704 Fields[5].Str = to_string(format_hex(Phdr.p_memsz, SizeWidth));
3705 Fields[6].Str = printPhdrFlags(Phdr.p_flags);
3706 Fields[7].Str = to_string(format_hex(Phdr.p_align, 1));
3707 for (auto Field : Fields)
3708 printField(Field);
3709 if (Phdr.p_type == ELF::PT_INTERP) {
3710 OS << "\n [Requesting program interpreter: ";
3711 OS << reinterpret_cast<const char *>(Obj->base()) + Phdr.p_offset << "]";
3712 }
3713 OS << "\n";
3714 }
3715}
3716
3717template <class ELFT>
3718void GNUStyle<ELFT>::printSectionMapping(const ELFO *Obj) {
3719 OS << "\n Section to Segment mapping:\n Segment Sections...\n";
3720 DenseSet<const Elf_Shdr *> BelongsToSegment;
3721 int Phnum = 0;
3722 for (const Elf_Phdr &Phdr : unwrapOrError(Obj->program_headers())) {
3723 std::string Sections;
3724 OS << format(" %2.2d ", Phnum++);
3725 for (const Elf_Shdr &Sec : unwrapOrError(Obj->sections())) {
3726 // Check if each section is in a segment and then print mapping.
3727 // readelf additionally makes sure it does not print zero sized sections
3728 // at end of segments and for PT_DYNAMIC both start and end of section
3729 // .tbss must only be shown in PT_TLS section.
3730 bool TbssInNonTLS = (Sec.sh_type == ELF::SHT_NOBITS) &&
3731 ((Sec.sh_flags & ELF::SHF_TLS) != 0) &&
3732 Phdr.p_type != ELF::PT_TLS;
3733 if (!TbssInNonTLS && checkTLSSections(Phdr, Sec) &&
3734 checkoffsets(Phdr, Sec) && checkVMA(Phdr, Sec) &&
3735 checkPTDynamic(Phdr, Sec) && (Sec.sh_type != ELF::SHT_NULL)) {
3736 Sections += unwrapOrError(Obj->getSectionName(&Sec)).str() + " ";
3737 BelongsToSegment.insert(&Sec);
3738 }
3739 }
3740 OS << Sections << "\n";
3741 OS.flush();
3742 }
3743
3744 // Display sections that do not belong to a segment.
3745 std::string Sections;
3746 for (const Elf_Shdr &Sec : unwrapOrError(Obj->sections())) {
3747 if (BelongsToSegment.find(&Sec) == BelongsToSegment.end())
3748 Sections += unwrapOrError(Obj->getSectionName(&Sec)).str() + ' ';
3749 }
3750 if (!Sections.empty()) {
3751 OS << " None " << Sections << '\n';
3752 OS.flush();
3753 }
3754}
3755
3756template <class ELFT>
3757void GNUStyle<ELFT>::printDynamicRelocation(const ELFO *Obj, Elf_Rela R,
3758 bool IsRela) {
3759 uint32_t SymIndex = R.getSymbol(Obj->isMips64EL());
3760 const Elf_Sym *Sym = this->dumper()->dynamic_symbols().begin() + SymIndex;
3761 std::string SymbolName = maybeDemangle(
3762 unwrapOrError(Sym->getName(this->dumper()->getDynamicStringTable())));
3763 printRelocation(Obj, Sym, SymbolName, R, IsRela);
3764}
3765
3766template <class ELFT> void GNUStyle<ELFT>::printDynamic(const ELFO *Obj) {
3767 Elf_Dyn_Range Table = this->dumper()->dynamic_table();
3768 if (Table.empty())
3769 return;
3770
3771 const DynRegionInfo &DynamicTableRegion =
3772 this->dumper()->getDynamicTableRegion();
3773
3774 OS << "Dynamic section at offset "
3775 << format_hex(reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t *>(DynamicTableRegion.Addr) -
3776 Obj->base(),
3777 1)
3778 << " contains " << Table.size() << " entries:\n";
3779
3780 bool Is64 = ELFT::Is64Bits;
3781 if (Is64)
3782 OS << " Tag Type Name/Value\n";
3783 else
3784 OS << " Tag Type Name/Value\n";
3785 for (auto Entry : Table) {
3786 uintX_t Tag = Entry.getTag();
3787 std::string TypeString = std::string("(") +
3788 getTypeString(Obj->getHeader()->e_machine, Tag) +
3789 ")";
3790 OS << " " << format_hex(Tag, Is64 ? 18 : 10)
3791 << format(" %-20s ", TypeString.c_str());
3792 this->dumper()->printDynamicEntry(OS, Tag, Entry.getVal());
3793 OS << "\n";
3794 }
3795}
3796
3797template <class ELFT>
3798void GNUStyle<ELFT>::printDynamicRelocations(const ELFO *Obj) {
3799 const DynRegionInfo &DynRelRegion = this->dumper()->getDynRelRegion();
3800 const DynRegionInfo &DynRelaRegion = this->dumper()->getDynRelaRegion();
3801 const DynRegionInfo &DynRelrRegion = this->dumper()->getDynRelrRegion();
3802 const DynRegionInfo &DynPLTRelRegion = this->dumper()->getDynPLTRelRegion();
3803 if (DynRelaRegion.Size > 0) {
3804 OS << "\n'RELA' relocation section at offset "
3805 << format_hex(reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t *>(DynRelaRegion.Addr) -
3806 Obj->base(),
3807 1)
3808 << " contains " << DynRelaRegion.Size << " bytes:\n";
3809 printRelocHeader(ELF::SHT_RELA);
3810 for (const Elf_Rela &Rela : this->dumper()->dyn_relas())
3811 printDynamicRelocation(Obj, Rela, true);
3812 }
3813 if (DynRelRegion.Size > 0) {
3814 OS << "\n'REL' relocation section at offset "
3815 << format_hex(reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t *>(DynRelRegion.Addr) -
3816 Obj->base(),
3817 1)
3818 << " contains " << DynRelRegion.Size << " bytes:\n";
3819 printRelocHeader(ELF::SHT_REL);
3820 for (const Elf_Rel &Rel : this->dumper()->dyn_rels()) {
3821 Elf_Rela Rela;
3822 Rela.r_offset = Rel.r_offset;
3823 Rela.r_info = Rel.r_info;
3824 Rela.r_addend = 0; // FIXME: this is wrong
3825 printDynamicRelocation(Obj, Rela, false);
3826 }
3827 }
3828 if (DynRelrRegion.Size > 0) {
3829 OS << "\n'RELR' relocation section at offset "
3830 << format_hex(reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t *>(DynRelrRegion.Addr) -
3831 Obj->base(),
3832 1)
3833 << " contains " << DynRelrRegion.Size << " bytes:\n";
3834 printRelocHeader(ELF::SHT_REL);
3835 Elf_Relr_Range Relrs = this->dumper()->dyn_relrs();
3836 std::vector<Elf_Rela> RelrRelas = unwrapOrError(Obj->decode_relrs(Relrs));
3837 for (const Elf_Rela &Rela : RelrRelas) {
3838 printDynamicRelocation(Obj, Rela, false);
3839 }
3840 }
3841 if (DynPLTRelRegion.Size) {
3842 OS << "\n'PLT' relocation section at offset "
3843 << format_hex(reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t *>(DynPLTRelRegion.Addr) -
3844 Obj->base(),
3845 1)
3846 << " contains " << DynPLTRelRegion.Size << " bytes:\n";
3847 }
3848 if (DynPLTRelRegion.EntSize == sizeof(Elf_Rela)) {
3849 printRelocHeader(ELF::SHT_RELA);
3850 for (const Elf_Rela &Rela : DynPLTRelRegion.getAsArrayRef<Elf_Rela>())
3851 printDynamicRelocation(Obj, Rela, true);
3852 } else {
3853 printRelocHeader(ELF::SHT_REL);
3854 for (const Elf_Rel &Rel : DynPLTRelRegion.getAsArrayRef<Elf_Rel>()) {
3855 Elf_Rela Rela;
3856 Rela.r_offset = Rel.r_offset;
3857 Rela.r_info = Rel.r_info;
3858 Rela.r_addend = 0;
3859 printDynamicRelocation(Obj, Rela, false);
3860 }
3861 }
3862}

3864template <class ELFT>
3865static void printGNUVersionSectionProlog(formatted_raw_ostream &OS,
3866 const Twine &Name, unsigned EntriesNum,
3867 const ELFFile<ELFT> *Obj,
3868 const typename ELFT::Shdr *Sec) {
3869 StringRef SecName = unwrapOrError(Obj->getSectionName(Sec));
3870 OS << Name << " section '" << SecName << "' "
3871 << "contains " << EntriesNum << " entries:\n";
3872
3873 const typename ELFT::Shdr *SymTab =
3874 unwrapOrError(Obj->getSection(Sec->sh_link));
3875 StringRef SymTabName = unwrapOrError(Obj->getSectionName(SymTab));
3876 OS << " Addr: " << format_hex_no_prefix(Sec->sh_addr, 16)
3877 << " Offset: " << format_hex(Sec->sh_offset, 8)
3878 << " Link: " << Sec->sh_link << " (" << SymTabName << ")\n";
3879}
3880
3881template <class ELFT>
3882void GNUStyle<ELFT>::printVersionSymbolSection(const ELFFile<ELFT> *Obj,
3883 const Elf_Shdr *Sec) {
3884 if (!Sec)
3885 return;
3886
3887 unsigned Entries = Sec->sh_size / sizeof(Elf_Versym);
3888 printGNUVersionSectionProlog(OS, "Version symbols", Entries, Obj, Sec);
3889
3890 const uint8_t *VersymBuf =
3891 reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t *>(Obj->base() + Sec->sh_offset);
3892 const ELFDumper<ELFT> *Dumper = this->dumper();
3893 StringRef StrTable = Dumper->getDynamicStringTable();
3894
3895 // readelf prints 4 entries per line.
3896 for (uint64_t VersymRow = 0; VersymRow < Entries; VersymRow += 4) {
3897 OS << " " << format_hex_no_prefix(VersymRow, 3) << ":";
3898
3899 for (uint64_t VersymIndex = 0;
3900 (VersymIndex < 4) && (VersymIndex + VersymRow) < Entries;
3901 ++VersymIndex) {
3902 const Elf_Versym *Versym =
3903 reinterpret_cast<const Elf_Versym *>(VersymBuf);
3904 switch (Versym->vs_index) {
3905 case 0:
3906 OS << " 0 (*local*) ";
3907 break;
3908 case 1:
3909 OS << " 1 (*global*) ";
3910 break;
3911 default:
3912 OS << format("%4x%c", Versym->vs_index & VERSYM_VERSION,
3913 Versym->vs_index & VERSYM_HIDDEN ? 'h' : ' ');
3914
3915 bool IsDefault = true;
3916 std::string VersionName = Dumper->getSymbolVersionByIndex(
3917 StrTable, Versym->vs_index, IsDefault);
3918
3919 if (!VersionName.empty())
3920 VersionName = "(" + VersionName + ")";
3921 else
3922 VersionName = "(*invalid*)";
3923 OS << left_justify(VersionName, 13);
3924 }
3925 VersymBuf += sizeof(Elf_Versym);
3926 }
3927 OS << '\n';
3928 }
3929 OS << '\n';
3930}
3931
3932static std::string versionFlagToString(unsigned Flags) {
3933 if (Flags == 0)
3934 return "none";
3935
3936 std::string Ret;
3937 auto AddFlag = [&Ret, &Flags](unsigned Flag, StringRef Name) {
3938 if (!(Flags & Flag))
3939 return;
3940 if (!Ret.empty())
3941 Ret += " | ";
3942 Ret += Name;
3943 Flags &= ~Flag;
3944 };
3945
3946 AddFlag(VER_FLG_BASE, "BASE");
3947 AddFlag(VER_FLG_WEAK, "WEAK");
3948 AddFlag(VER_FLG_INFO, "INFO");
3949 AddFlag(~0, "<unknown>");
3950 return Ret;
3951}
3952
3953template <class ELFT>
3954void GNUStyle<ELFT>::printVersionDefinitionSection(const ELFFile<ELFT> *Obj,
3955 const Elf_Shdr *Sec) {
3956 if (!Sec)
3957 return;
3958
3959 unsigned VerDefsNum = Sec->sh_info;
3960 printGNUVersionSectionProlog(OS, "Version definition", VerDefsNum, Obj, Sec);
3961
3962 const Elf_Shdr *StrTabSec = unwrapOrError(Obj->getSection(Sec->sh_link));
3963 StringRef StringTable(
3964 reinterpret_cast<const char *>(Obj->base() + StrTabSec->sh_offset),
3965 (size_t)StrTabSec->sh_size);
3966
3967 const uint8_t *VerdefBuf = unwrapOrError(Obj->getSectionContents(Sec)).data();
3968 const uint8_t *Begin = VerdefBuf;
3969
3970 while (VerDefsNum--) {
3971 const Elf_Verdef *Verdef = reinterpret_cast<const Elf_Verdef *>(VerdefBuf);
3972 OS << format(" 0x%04x: Rev: %u Flags: %s Index: %u Cnt: %u",
3973 VerdefBuf - Begin, (unsigned)Verdef->vd_version,
3974 versionFlagToString(Verdef->vd_flags).c_str(),
3975 (unsigned)Verdef->vd_ndx, (unsigned)Verdef->vd_cnt);
3976
3977 const uint8_t *VerdauxBuf = VerdefBuf + Verdef->vd_aux;
3978 const Elf_Verdaux *Verdaux =
3979 reinterpret_cast<const Elf_Verdaux *>(VerdauxBuf);
3980 OS << format(" Name: %s\n",
3981 StringTable.drop_front(Verdaux->vda_name).data());
3982
3983 for (unsigned I = 1; I < Verdef->vd_cnt; ++I) {
3984 VerdauxBuf += Verdaux->vda_next;
3985 Verdaux = reinterpret_cast<const Elf_Verdaux *>(VerdauxBuf);
3986 OS << format(" 0x%04x: Parent %u: %s\n", VerdauxBuf - Begin, I,
3987 StringTable.drop_front(Verdaux->vda_name).data());
3988 }
3989
3990 VerdefBuf += Verdef->vd_next;
3991 }
3992 OS << '\n';
3993}

3995template <class ELFT>
3996void GNUStyle<ELFT>::printVersionDependencySection(const ELFFile<ELFT> *Obj,
3997 const Elf_Shdr *Sec) {
3998 if (!Sec)
3999 return;
4000
4001 unsigned VerneedNum = Sec->sh_info;
4002 printGNUVersionSectionProlog(OS, "Version needs", VerneedNum, Obj, Sec);
4003
4004 ArrayRef<uint8_t> SecData = unwrapOrError(Obj->getSectionContents(Sec));
4005
4006 const Elf_Shdr *StrTabSec = unwrapOrError(Obj->getSection(Sec->sh_link));
4007 StringRef StringTable = {
4008 reinterpret_cast<const char *>(Obj->base() + StrTabSec->sh_offset),
4009 (size_t)StrTabSec->sh_size};
4010
4011 const uint8_t *VerneedBuf = SecData.data();
4012 for (unsigned I = 0; I < VerneedNum; ++I) {
4013 const Elf_Verneed *Verneed =
4014 reinterpret_cast<const Elf_Verneed *>(VerneedBuf);
4015
4016 OS << format(" 0x%04x: Version: %u File: %s Cnt: %u\n",
4017 reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t *>(Verneed) - SecData.begin(),
4018 (unsigned)Verneed->vn_version,
4019 StringTable.drop_front(Verneed->vn_file).data(),
4020 (unsigned)Verneed->vn_cnt);
4021
4022 const uint8_t *VernauxBuf = VerneedBuf + Verneed->vn_aux;
4023 for (unsigned J = 0; J < Verneed->vn_cnt; ++J) {
4024 const Elf_Vernaux *Vernaux =
4025 reinterpret_cast<const Elf_Vernaux *>(VernauxBuf);
4026
4027 OS << format(" 0x%04x: Name: %s Flags: %s Version: %u\n",
4028 reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t *>(Vernaux) - SecData.begin(),
4029 StringTable.drop_front(Vernaux->vna_name).data(),
4030 versionFlagToString(Vernaux->vna_flags).c_str(),
4031 (unsigned)Vernaux->vna_other);
4032 VernauxBuf += Vernaux->vna_next;
4033 }
4034 VerneedBuf += Verneed->vn_next;
4035 }
4036 OS << '\n';
4037}
4038
4039// Hash histogram shows statistics of how efficient the hash was for the
4040// dynamic symbol table. The table shows number of hash buckets for different
4041// lengths of chains as absolute number and percentage of the total buckets.
4042// Additionally cumulative coverage of symbols for each set of buckets.
4043template <class ELFT>
4044void GNUStyle<ELFT>::printHashHistogram(const ELFFile<ELFT> *Obj) {
4045 // Print histogram for .hash section
4046 if (const Elf_Hash *HashTable = this->dumper()->getHashTable()) {
4047 size_t NBucket = HashTable->nbucket;
4048 size_t NChain = HashTable->nchain;
4049 ArrayRef<Elf_Word> Buckets = HashTable->buckets();
4050 ArrayRef<Elf_Word> Chains = HashTable->chains();
4051 size_t TotalSyms = 0;
4052 // If hash table is correct, we have at least chains with 0 length
4053 size_t MaxChain = 1;
4054 size_t CumulativeNonZero = 0;
4055
4056 if (NChain == 0 || NBucket == 0)
4057 return;
4058
4059 std::vector<size_t> ChainLen(NBucket, 0);
4060 // Go over all buckets and and note chain lengths of each bucket (total
4061 // unique chain lengths).
4062 for (size_t B = 0; B < NBucket; B++) {
4063 for (size_t C = Buckets[B]; C > 0 && C < NChain; C = Chains[C])
4064 if (MaxChain <= ++ChainLen[B])
4065 MaxChain++;
4066 TotalSyms += ChainLen[B];
4067 }
4068
4069 if (!TotalSyms)
4070 return;
4071
4072 std::vector<size_t> Count(MaxChain, 0) ;
4073 // Count how long is the chain for each bucket
4074 for (size_t B = 0; B < NBucket; B++)
4075 ++Count[ChainLen[B]];
4076 // Print Number of buckets with each chain lengths and their cumulative
4077 // coverage of the symbols
4078 OS << "Histogram for bucket list length (total of " << NBucket
4079 << " buckets)\n"
4080 << " Length Number % of total Coverage\n";
4081 for (size_t I = 0; I < MaxChain; I++) {
4082 CumulativeNonZero += Count[I] * I;
4083 OS << format("%7lu %-10lu (%5.1f%%) %5.1f%%\n", I, Count[I],
4084 (Count[I] * 100.0) / NBucket,
4085 (CumulativeNonZero * 100.0) / TotalSyms);
4086 }
4087 }
4088
4089 // Print histogram for .gnu.hash section
4090 if (const Elf_GnuHash *GnuHashTable = this->dumper()->getGnuHashTable()) {
4091 size_t NBucket = GnuHashTable->nbuckets;
4092 ArrayRef<Elf_Word> Buckets = GnuHashTable->buckets();
4093 unsigned NumSyms = this->dumper()->dynamic_symbols().size();
4094 if (!NumSyms)
4095 return;
4096 ArrayRef<Elf_Word> Chains = GnuHashTable->values(NumSyms);
4097 size_t Symndx = GnuHashTable->symndx;
4098 size_t TotalSyms = 0;
4099 size_t MaxChain = 1;
4100 size_t CumulativeNonZero = 0;
4101
4102 if (Chains.empty() || NBucket == 0)
4103 return;
4104
4105 std::vector<size_t> ChainLen(NBucket, 0);
4106
4107 for (size_t B = 0; B < NBucket; B++) {
4108 if (!Buckets[B])
4109 continue;
4110 size_t Len = 1;
4111 for (size_t C = Buckets[B] - Symndx;
4112 C < Chains.size() && (Chains[C] & 1) == 0; C++)
4113 if (MaxChain < ++Len)
4114 MaxChain++;
4115 ChainLen[B] = Len;
4116 TotalSyms += Len;
4117 }
4118 MaxChain++;
4119
4120 if (!TotalSyms)
4121 return;
4122
4123 std::vector<size_t> Count(MaxChain, 0) ;
4124 for (size_t B = 0; B < NBucket; B++)
4125 ++Count[ChainLen[B]];
4126 // Print Number of buckets with each chain lengths and their cumulative
4127 // coverage of the symbols
4128 OS << "Histogram for `.gnu.hash' bucket list length (total of " << NBucket
4129 << " buckets)\n"
4130 << " Length Number % of total Coverage\n";
4131 for (size_t I = 0; I <MaxChain; I++) {
4132 CumulativeNonZero += Count[I] * I;
4133 OS << format("%7lu %-10lu (%5.1f%%) %5.1f%%\n", I, Count[I],
4134 (Count[I] * 100.0) / NBucket,
4135 (CumulativeNonZero * 100.0) / TotalSyms);
4136 }
4137 }
4138}

4247
4248template <typename ELFT>
4249static std::string getGNUProperty(uint32_t Type, uint32_t DataSize,
4250 ArrayRef<uint8_t> Data) {
4251 std::string str;
4252 raw_string_ostream OS(str);
4253 uint32_t PrData;
4254 auto DumpBit = [&](uint32_t Flag, StringRef Name) {
4255 if (PrData & Flag) {
4256 PrData &= ~Flag;
4257 OS << Name;
4258 if (PrData)
4259 OS << ", ";
4260 }
4261 };
4262
4263 switch (Type) {
4264 default:
4265 OS << format("<application-specific type 0x%x>", Type);
4266 return OS.str();
4267 case GNU_PROPERTY_STACK_SIZE: {
4268 OS << "stack size: ";
4269 if (DataSize == sizeof(typename ELFT::uint))
4270 OS << formatv("{0:x}",
4271 (uint64_t)(*(const typename ELFT::Addr *)Data.data()));
4272 else
4273 OS << format("<corrupt length: 0x%x>", DataSize);
4274 return OS.str();
4275 }
4276 case GNU_PROPERTY_NO_COPY_ON_PROTECTED:
4277 OS << "no copy on protected";
4278 if (DataSize)
4279 OS << format(" <corrupt length: 0x%x>", DataSize);
4280 return OS.str();
4281 case GNU_PROPERTY_AARCH64_FEATURE_1_AND:
4282 case GNU_PROPERTY_X86_FEATURE_1_AND:
4283 OS << ((Type == GNU_PROPERTY_AARCH64_FEATURE_1_AND) ? "aarch64 feature: "
4284 : "x86 feature: ");
4285 if (DataSize != 4) {
4286 OS << format("<corrupt length: 0x%x>", DataSize);
4287 return OS.str();
4288 }
4289 PrData = support::endian::read32<ELFT::TargetEndianness>(Data.data());
4290 if (PrData == 0) {
4291 OS << "<None>";
4292 return OS.str();
4293 }
4294 if (Type == GNU_PROPERTY_AARCH64_FEATURE_1_AND) {
4295 DumpBit(GNU_PROPERTY_AARCH64_FEATURE_1_BTI, "BTI");
4296 DumpBit(GNU_PROPERTY_AARCH64_FEATURE_1_PAC, "PAC");
4297 } else {
4298 DumpBit(GNU_PROPERTY_X86_FEATURE_1_IBT, "IBT");
4299 DumpBit(GNU_PROPERTY_X86_FEATURE_1_SHSTK, "SHSTK");
4300 }
4301 if (PrData)
4302 OS << format("<unknown flags: 0x%x>", PrData);
4303 return OS.str();
4304 case GNU_PROPERTY_X86_ISA_1_NEEDED:
4305 case GNU_PROPERTY_X86_ISA_1_USED:
4306 OS << "x86 ISA "
4307 << (Type == GNU_PROPERTY_X86_ISA_1_NEEDED ? "needed: " : "used: ");
4308 if (DataSize != 4) {
4309 OS << format("<corrupt length: 0x%x>", DataSize);
4310 return OS.str();
4311 }
4312 PrData = support::endian::read32<ELFT::TargetEndianness>(Data.data());
4313 if (PrData == 0) {
4314 OS << "<None>";
4315 return OS.str();
4316 }
4317 DumpBit(GNU_PROPERTY_X86_ISA_1_CMOV, "CMOV");
4318 DumpBit(GNU_PROPERTY_X86_ISA_1_SSE, "SSE");
4319 DumpBit(GNU_PROPERTY_X86_ISA_1_SSE2, "SSE2");
4320 DumpBit(GNU_PROPERTY_X86_ISA_1_SSE3, "SSE3");
4321 DumpBit(GNU_PROPERTY_X86_ISA_1_SSSE3, "SSSE3");
4322 DumpBit(GNU_PROPERTY_X86_ISA_1_SSE4_1, "SSE4_1");
4323 DumpBit(GNU_PROPERTY_X86_ISA_1_SSE4_2, "SSE4_2");
4324 DumpBit(GNU_PROPERTY_X86_ISA_1_AVX, "AVX");
4325 DumpBit(GNU_PROPERTY_X86_ISA_1_AVX2, "AVX2");
4326 DumpBit(GNU_PROPERTY_X86_ISA_1_FMA, "FMA");
4327 DumpBit(GNU_PROPERTY_X86_ISA_1_AVX512F, "AVX512F");
4328 DumpBit(GNU_PROPERTY_X86_ISA_1_AVX512CD, "AVX512CD");
4329 DumpBit(GNU_PROPERTY_X86_ISA_1_AVX512ER, "AVX512ER");
4330 DumpBit(GNU_PROPERTY_X86_ISA_1_AVX512PF, "AVX512PF");
4331 DumpBit(GNU_PROPERTY_X86_ISA_1_AVX512VL, "AVX512VL");
4332 DumpBit(GNU_PROPERTY_X86_ISA_1_AVX512DQ, "AVX512DQ");
4333 DumpBit(GNU_PROPERTY_X86_ISA_1_AVX512BW, "AVX512BW");
4334 DumpBit(GNU_PROPERTY_X86_ISA_1_AVX512_4FMAPS, "AVX512_4FMAPS");
4335 DumpBit(GNU_PROPERTY_X86_ISA_1_AVX512_4VNNIW, "AVX512_4VNNIW");
4336 DumpBit(GNU_PROPERTY_X86_ISA_1_AVX512_BITALG, "AVX512_BITALG");
4337 DumpBit(GNU_PROPERTY_X86_ISA_1_AVX512_IFMA, "AVX512_IFMA");
4338 DumpBit(GNU_PROPERTY_X86_ISA_1_AVX512_VBMI, "AVX512_VBMI");
4339 DumpBit(GNU_PROPERTY_X86_ISA_1_AVX512_VBMI2, "AVX512_VBMI2");
4340 DumpBit(GNU_PROPERTY_X86_ISA_1_AVX512_VNNI, "AVX512_VNNI");
4341 if (PrData)
4342 OS << format("<unknown flags: 0x%x>", PrData);
4343 return OS.str();
4344 break;
4345 case GNU_PROPERTY_X86_FEATURE_2_NEEDED:
4346 case GNU_PROPERTY_X86_FEATURE_2_USED:
4347 OS << "x86 feature "
4348 << (Type == GNU_PROPERTY_X86_FEATURE_2_NEEDED ? "needed: " : "used: ");
4349 if (DataSize != 4) {
4350 OS << format("<corrupt length: 0x%x>", DataSize);
4351 return OS.str();
4352 }
4353 PrData = support::endian::read32<ELFT::TargetEndianness>(Data.data());
4354 if (PrData == 0) {
4355 OS << "<None>";
4356 return OS.str();
4357 }
4358 DumpBit(GNU_PROPERTY_X86_FEATURE_2_X86, "x86");
4359 DumpBit(GNU_PROPERTY_X86_FEATURE_2_X87, "x87");
4360 DumpBit(GNU_PROPERTY_X86_FEATURE_2_MMX, "MMX");
4361 DumpBit(GNU_PROPERTY_X86_FEATURE_2_XMM, "XMM");
4362 DumpBit(GNU_PROPERTY_X86_FEATURE_2_YMM, "YMM");
4363 DumpBit(GNU_PROPERTY_X86_FEATURE_2_ZMM, "ZMM");
4364 DumpBit(GNU_PROPERTY_X86_FEATURE_2_FXSR, "FXSR");
4365 DumpBit(GNU_PROPERTY_X86_FEATURE_2_XSAVE, "XSAVE");
4366 DumpBit(GNU_PROPERTY_X86_FEATURE_2_XSAVEOPT, "XSAVEOPT");
4367 DumpBit(GNU_PROPERTY_X86_FEATURE_2_XSAVEC, "XSAVEC");
4368 if (PrData)
4369 OS << format("<unknown flags: 0x%x>", PrData);
4370 return OS.str();
4371 }
4372}
4373
4374template <typename ELFT>
4375static SmallVector<std::string, 4> getGNUPropertyList(ArrayRef<uint8_t> Arr) {
4376 using Elf_Word = typename ELFT::Word;
4377
4378 SmallVector<std::string, 4> Properties;
4379 while (Arr.size() >= 8) {
4380 uint32_t Type = *reinterpret_cast<const Elf_Word *>(Arr.data());
4381 uint32_t DataSize = *reinterpret_cast<const Elf_Word *>(Arr.data() + 4);
4382 Arr = Arr.drop_front(8);
4383
4384 // Take padding size into account if present.
4385 uint64_t PaddedSize = alignTo(DataSize, sizeof(typename ELFT::uint));
4386 std::string str;
4387 raw_string_ostream OS(str);
4388 if (Arr.size() < PaddedSize) {
4389 OS << format("<corrupt type (0x%x) datasz: 0x%x>", Type, DataSize);
4390 Properties.push_back(OS.str());
4391 break;
4392 }
4393 Properties.push_back(
4394 getGNUProperty<ELFT>(Type, DataSize, Arr.take_front(PaddedSize)));
4395 Arr = Arr.drop_front(PaddedSize);
4396 }
4397
4398 if (!Arr.empty())
4399 Properties.push_back("<corrupted GNU_PROPERTY_TYPE_0>");
4400
4401 return Properties;
4402}
4403
4404struct GNUAbiTag {
4405 std::string OSName;
4406 std::string ABI;
4407 bool IsValid;
4408};
4409
4410template <typename ELFT> static GNUAbiTag getGNUAbiTag(ArrayRef<uint8_t> Desc) {
4411 typedef typename ELFT::Word Elf_Word;
4412
4413 ArrayRef<Elf_Word> Words(reinterpret_cast<const Elf_Word *>(Desc.begin()),
4414 reinterpret_cast<const Elf_Word *>(Desc.end()));
4415
4416 if (Words.size() < 4)
4417 return {"", "", /*IsValid=*/false};
4418
4419 static const char *OSNames[] = {
4420 "Linux", "Hurd", "Solaris", "FreeBSD", "NetBSD", "Syllable", "NaCl",
4421 };
4422 StringRef OSName = "Unknown";
4423 if (Words[0] < array_lengthof(OSNames))
4424 OSName = OSNames[Words[0]];
4425 uint32_t Major = Words[1], Minor = Words[2], Patch = Words[3];
4426 std::string str;
4427 raw_string_ostream ABI(str);
4428 ABI << Major << "." << Minor << "." << Patch;
4429 return {OSName, ABI.str(), /*IsValid=*/true};
4430}
4431
4432static std::string getGNUBuildId(ArrayRef<uint8_t> Desc) {
4433 std::string str;
4434 raw_string_ostream OS(str);
4435 for (const auto &B : Desc)
4436 OS << format_hex_no_prefix(B, 2);
4437 return OS.str();
4438}
4439
4440static StringRef getGNUGoldVersion(ArrayRef<uint8_t> Desc) {
4441 return StringRef(reinterpret_cast<const char *>(Desc.data()), Desc.size());
4442}
4443
4444template <typename ELFT>
4445static void printGNUNote(raw_ostream &OS, uint32_t NoteType,
4446 ArrayRef<uint8_t> Desc) {
4447 switch (NoteType) {
4448 default:
4449 return;
4450 case ELF::NT_GNU_ABI_TAG: {
4451 const GNUAbiTag &AbiTag = getGNUAbiTag<ELFT>(Desc);
4452 if (!AbiTag.IsValid)
4453 OS << " <corrupt GNU_ABI_TAG>";
4454 else
4455 OS << " OS: " << AbiTag.OSName << ", ABI: " << AbiTag.ABI;
4456 break;
4457 }
4458 case ELF::NT_GNU_BUILD_ID: {
4459 OS << " Build ID: " << getGNUBuildId(Desc);
4460 break;
4461 }
4462 case ELF::NT_GNU_GOLD_VERSION:
4463 OS << " Version: " << getGNUGoldVersion(Desc);
4464 break;
4465 case ELF::NT_GNU_PROPERTY_TYPE_0:
4466 OS << " Properties:";
4467 for (const auto &Property : getGNUPropertyList<ELFT>(Desc))
4468 OS << " " << Property << "\n";
4469 break;
4470 }
4471 OS << '\n';
4472}

4474struct AMDNote {
4475 std::string Type;
4476 std::string Value;
4477};
4478
4479template <typename ELFT>
4480static AMDNote getAMDNote(uint32_t NoteType, ArrayRef<uint8_t> Desc) {
4481 switch (NoteType) {
4482 default:
4483 return {"", ""};
4484 case ELF::NT_AMD_AMDGPU_HSA_METADATA:
4485 return {
4486 "HSA Metadata",
4487 std::string(reinterpret_cast<const char *>(Desc.data()), Desc.size())};
4488 case ELF::NT_AMD_AMDGPU_ISA:
4489 return {
4490 "ISA Version",
4491 std::string(reinterpret_cast<const char *>(Desc.data()), Desc.size())};
4492 }
4493}
4494
4495struct AMDGPUNote {
4496 std::string Type;
4497 std::string Value;
4498};
4499
4500template <typename ELFT>
4501static AMDGPUNote getAMDGPUNote(uint32_t NoteType, ArrayRef<uint8_t> Desc) {
4502 switch (NoteType) {
4503 default:
4504 return {"", ""};
4505 case ELF::NT_AMDGPU_METADATA: {
4506 auto MsgPackString =
4507 StringRef(reinterpret_cast<const char *>(Desc.data()), Desc.size());
4508 msgpack::Document MsgPackDoc;
4509 if (!MsgPackDoc.readFromBlob(MsgPackString, /*Multi=*/false))
4510 return {"AMDGPU Metadata", "Invalid AMDGPU Metadata"};
4511
4512 AMDGPU::HSAMD::V3::MetadataVerifier Verifier(true);
4513 if (!Verifier.verify(MsgPackDoc.getRoot()))
4514 return {"AMDGPU Metadata", "Invalid AMDGPU Metadata"};
4515
4516 std::string HSAMetadataString;
4517 raw_string_ostream StrOS(HSAMetadataString);
4518 MsgPackDoc.toYAML(StrOS);
4519
4520 return {"AMDGPU Metadata", StrOS.str()};
4521 }
4522 }
4523}

4525template <class ELFT>
4526void GNUStyle<ELFT>::printNotes(const ELFFile<ELFT> *Obj) {
4527 auto PrintHeader = [&](const typename ELFT::Off Offset,
4528 const typename ELFT::Addr Size) {
4529 OS << "Displaying notes found at file offset " << format_hex(Offset, 10)
4530 << " with length " << format_hex(Size, 10) << ":\n"
4531 << " Owner Data size\tDescription\n";
4532 };
4533
4534 auto ProcessNote = [&](const Elf_Note &Note) {
4535 StringRef Name = Note.getName();
4536 ArrayRef<uint8_t> Descriptor = Note.getDesc();
4537 Elf_Word Type = Note.getType();
4538
4539 OS << " " << Name << std::string(22 - Name.size(), ' ')
4540 << format_hex(Descriptor.size(), 10) << '\t';
4541
4542 if (Name == "GNU") {
4543 OS << getGNUNoteTypeName(Type) << '\n';
4544 printGNUNote<ELFT>(OS, Type, Descriptor);
4545 } else if (Name == "FreeBSD") {
4546 OS << getFreeBSDNoteTypeName(Type) << '\n';
4547 } else if (Name == "AMD") {
4548 OS << getAMDNoteTypeName(Type) << '\n';
4549 const AMDNote N = getAMDNote<ELFT>(Type, Descriptor);
4550 if (!N.Type.empty())
4551 OS << " " << N.Type << ":\n " << N.Value << '\n';
4552 } else if (Name == "AMDGPU") {
4553 OS << getAMDGPUNoteTypeName(Type) << '\n';
4554 const AMDGPUNote N = getAMDGPUNote<ELFT>(Type, Descriptor);
4555 if (!N.Type.empty())
4556 OS << " " << N.Type << ":\n " << N.Value << '\n';
4557 } else {
4558 StringRef NoteType = getGenericNoteTypeName(Type);
4559 if (!NoteType.empty())
4560 OS << NoteType;
4561 else
4562 OS << "Unknown note type: (" << format_hex(Type, 10) << ')';
4563 }
4564 OS << '\n';
4565 };
4566
4567 if (Obj->getHeader()->e_type == ELF::ET_CORE) {
4568 for (const auto &P : unwrapOrError(Obj->program_headers())) {
4569 if (P.p_type != PT_NOTE)
4570 continue;
4571 PrintHeader(P.p_offset, P.p_filesz);
4572 Error Err = Error::success();
4573 for (const auto &Note : Obj->notes(P, Err))
4574 ProcessNote(Note);
4575 if (Err)
4576 error(std::move(Err));
4577 }
4578 } else {
4579 for (const auto &S : unwrapOrError(Obj->sections())) {
4580 if (S.sh_type != SHT_NOTE)
4581 continue;
4582 PrintHeader(S.sh_offset, S.sh_size);
4583 Error Err = Error::success();
4584 for (const auto &Note : Obj->notes(S, Err))
4585 ProcessNote(Note);
4586 if (Err)
4587 error(std::move(Err));
4588 }
4589 }
4590}

4594 OS << "printELFLinkerOptions not implemented!\n";

4597template <class ELFT>
4598void GNUStyle<ELFT>::printMipsGOT(const MipsGOTParser<ELFT> &Parser) {
4599 size_t Bias = ELFT::Is64Bits ? 8 : 0;
4600 auto PrintEntry = [&](const Elf_Addr *E, StringRef Purpose) {
4601 OS.PadToColumn(2);
4602 OS << format_hex_no_prefix(Parser.getGotAddress(E), 8 + Bias);
4603 OS.PadToColumn(11 + Bias);
4604 OS << format_decimal(Parser.getGotOffset(E), 6) << "(gp)";
4605 OS.PadToColumn(22 + Bias);
4606 OS << format_hex_no_prefix(*E, 8 + Bias);
4607 OS.PadToColumn(31 + 2 * Bias);
4608 OS << Purpose << "\n";
4609 };
4610
4611 OS << (Parser.IsStatic ? "Static GOT:\n" : "Primary GOT:\n");
4612 OS << " Canonical gp value: "
4613 << format_hex_no_prefix(Parser.getGp(), 8 + Bias) << "\n\n";
4614
4615 OS << " Reserved entries:\n";
4616 if (ELFT::Is64Bits)
4617 OS << " Address Access Initial Purpose\n";
4618 else
4619 OS << " Address Access Initial Purpose\n";
4620 PrintEntry(Parser.getGotLazyResolver(), "Lazy resolver");
4621 if (Parser.getGotModulePointer())
4622 PrintEntry(Parser.getGotModulePointer(), "Module pointer (GNU extension)");
4623
4624 if (!Parser.getLocalEntries().empty()) {
4625 OS << "\n";
4626 OS << " Local entries:\n";
4627 if (ELFT::Is64Bits)
4628 OS << " Address Access Initial\n";
4629 else
4630 OS << " Address Access Initial\n";
4631 for (auto &E : Parser.getLocalEntries())
4632 PrintEntry(&E, "");
4633 }
4634
4635 if (Parser.IsStatic)
4636 return;
4637
4638 if (!Parser.getGlobalEntries().empty()) {
4639 OS << "\n";
4640 OS << " Global entries:\n";
4641 if (ELFT::Is64Bits)
4642 OS << " Address Access Initial Sym.Val."
4643 << " Type Ndx Name\n";
4644 else
4645 OS << " Address Access Initial Sym.Val. Type Ndx Name\n";
4646 for (auto &E : Parser.getGlobalEntries()) {
4647 const Elf_Sym *Sym = Parser.getGotSym(&E);
4648 std::string SymName = this->dumper()->getFullSymbolName(
4649 Sym, this->dumper()->getDynamicStringTable(), false);
4650
4651 OS.PadToColumn(2);
4652 OS << to_string(format_hex_no_prefix(Parser.getGotAddress(&E), 8 + Bias));
4653 OS.PadToColumn(11 + Bias);
4654 OS << to_string(format_decimal(Parser.getGotOffset(&E), 6)) + "(gp)";
4655 OS.PadToColumn(22 + Bias);
4656 OS << to_string(format_hex_no_prefix(E, 8 + Bias));
4657 OS.PadToColumn(31 + 2 * Bias);
4658 OS << to_string(format_hex_no_prefix(Sym->st_value, 8 + Bias));
4659 OS.PadToColumn(40 + 3 * Bias);
4660 OS << printEnum(Sym->getType(), makeArrayRef(ElfSymbolTypes));
4661 OS.PadToColumn(48 + 3 * Bias);
4662 OS << getSymbolSectionNdx(Parser.Obj, Sym,
4663 this->dumper()->dynamic_symbols().begin());
4664 OS.PadToColumn(52 + 3 * Bias);
4665 OS << SymName << "\n";
4666 }
4667 }
4668
4669 if (!Parser.getOtherEntries().empty())
4670 OS << "\n Number of TLS and multi-GOT entries "
4671 << Parser.getOtherEntries().size() << "\n";
4672}
4673
4674template <class ELFT>
4675void GNUStyle<ELFT>::printMipsPLT(const MipsGOTParser<ELFT> &Parser) {
4676 size_t Bias = ELFT::Is64Bits ? 8 : 0;
4677 auto PrintEntry = [&](const Elf_Addr *E, StringRef Purpose) {
4678 OS.PadToColumn(2);
4679 OS << format_hex_no_prefix(Parser.getPltAddress(E), 8 + Bias);
4680 OS.PadToColumn(11 + Bias);
4681 OS << format_hex_no_prefix(*E, 8 + Bias);
4682 OS.PadToColumn(20 + 2 * Bias);
4683 OS << Purpose << "\n";
4684 };
4685
4686 OS << "PLT GOT:\n\n";
4687
4688 OS << " Reserved entries:\n";
4689 OS << " Address Initial Purpose\n";
4690 PrintEntry(Parser.getPltLazyResolver(), "PLT lazy resolver");
4691 if (Parser.getPltModulePointer())
4692 PrintEntry(Parser.getPltModulePointer(), "Module pointer");
4693
4694 if (!Parser.getPltEntries().empty()) {
4695 OS << "\n";
4696 OS << " Entries:\n";
4697 OS << " Address Initial Sym.Val. Type Ndx Name\n";
4698 for (auto &E : Parser.getPltEntries()) {
4699 const Elf_Sym *Sym = Parser.getPltSym(&E);
4700 std::string SymName = this->dumper()->getFullSymbolName(
4701 Sym, this->dumper()->getDynamicStringTable(), false);
4702
4703 OS.PadToColumn(2);
4704 OS << to_string(format_hex_no_prefix(Parser.getPltAddress(&E), 8 + Bias));
4705 OS.PadToColumn(11 + Bias);
4706 OS << to_string(format_hex_no_prefix(E, 8 + Bias));
4707 OS.PadToColumn(20 + 2 * Bias);
4708 OS << to_string(format_hex_no_prefix(Sym->st_value, 8 + Bias));
4709 OS.PadToColumn(29 + 3 * Bias);
4710 OS << printEnum(Sym->getType(), makeArrayRef(ElfSymbolTypes));
4711 OS.PadToColumn(37 + 3 * Bias);
4712 OS << getSymbolSectionNdx(Parser.Obj, Sym,
4713 this->dumper()->dynamic_symbols().begin());
4714 OS.PadToColumn(41 + 3 * Bias);
4715 OS << SymName << "\n";
4716 }
4717 }

4720template <class ELFT> void LLVMStyle<ELFT>::printFileHeaders(const ELFO *Obj) {
4721 const Elf_Ehdr *E = Obj->getHeader();
4722 {
4723 DictScope D(W, "ElfHeader");
4724 {
4725 DictScope D(W, "Ident");
4726 W.printBinary("Magic", makeArrayRef(E->e_ident).slice(ELF::EI_MAG0, 4));
4727 W.printEnum("Class", E->e_ident[ELF::EI_CLASS], makeArrayRef(ElfClass));
4728 W.printEnum("DataEncoding", E->e_ident[ELF::EI_DATA],
4729 makeArrayRef(ElfDataEncoding));
4730 W.printNumber("FileVersion", E->e_ident[ELF::EI_VERSION]);
4731
4732 auto OSABI = makeArrayRef(ElfOSABI);
4733 if (E->e_ident[ELF::EI_OSABI] >= ELF::ELFOSABI_FIRST_ARCH &&
4734 E->e_ident[ELF::EI_OSABI] <= ELF::ELFOSABI_LAST_ARCH) {
4735 switch (E->e_machine) {
4736 case ELF::EM_AMDGPU:
4737 OSABI = makeArrayRef(AMDGPUElfOSABI);
4738 break;
4739 case ELF::EM_ARM:
4740 OSABI = makeArrayRef(ARMElfOSABI);
4741 break;
4742 case ELF::EM_TI_C6000:
4743 OSABI = makeArrayRef(C6000ElfOSABI);
4744 break;
4745 }
4746 }
4747 W.printEnum("OS/ABI", E->e_ident[ELF::EI_OSABI], OSABI);
4748 W.printNumber("ABIVersion", E->e_ident[ELF::EI_ABIVERSION]);
4749 W.printBinary("Unused", makeArrayRef(E->e_ident).slice(ELF::EI_PAD));
4750 }
4751
4752 W.printEnum("Type", E->e_type, makeArrayRef(ElfObjectFileType));
4753 W.printEnum("Machine", E->e_machine, makeArrayRef(ElfMachineType));
4754 W.printNumber("Version", E->e_version);
4755 W.printHex("Entry", E->e_entry);
4756 W.printHex("ProgramHeaderOffset", E->e_phoff);
4757 W.printHex("SectionHeaderOffset", E->e_shoff);
4758 if (E->e_machine == EM_MIPS)
4759 W.printFlags("Flags", E->e_flags, makeArrayRef(ElfHeaderMipsFlags),
4760 unsigned(ELF::EF_MIPS_ARCH), unsigned(ELF::EF_MIPS_ABI),
4761 unsigned(ELF::EF_MIPS_MACH));
4762 else if (E->e_machine == EM_AMDGPU)
4763 W.printFlags("Flags", E->e_flags, makeArrayRef(ElfHeaderAMDGPUFlags),
4764 unsigned(ELF::EF_AMDGPU_MACH));
4765 else if (E->e_machine == EM_RISCV)
4766 W.printFlags("Flags", E->e_flags, makeArrayRef(ElfHeaderRISCVFlags));
4767 else
4768 W.printFlags("Flags", E->e_flags);
4769 W.printNumber("HeaderSize", E->e_ehsize);
4770 W.printNumber("ProgramHeaderEntrySize", E->e_phentsize);
4771 W.printNumber("ProgramHeaderCount", E->e_phnum);
4772 W.printNumber("SectionHeaderEntrySize", E->e_shentsize);
4773 W.printString("SectionHeaderCount", getSectionHeadersNumString(Obj));
4774 W.printString("StringTableSectionIndex",
4775 getSectionHeaderTableIndexString(Obj));
4776 }
4777}

4779template <class ELFT>
4780void LLVMStyle<ELFT>::printGroupSections(const ELFO *Obj) {
4781 DictScope Lists(W, "Groups");
4782 std::vector<GroupSection> V = getGroups<ELFT>(Obj);
4783 DenseMap<uint64_t, const GroupSection *> Map = mapSectionsToGroups(V);
4784 for (const GroupSection &G : V) {
4785 DictScope D(W, "Group");
4786 W.printNumber("Name", G.Name, G.ShName);
4787 W.printNumber("Index", G.Index);
4788 W.printNumber("Link", G.Link);
4789 W.printNumber("Info", G.Info);
4790 W.printHex("Type", getGroupType(G.Type), G.Type);
4791 W.startLine() << "Signature: " << G.Signature << "\n";
4792
4793 ListScope L(W, "Section(s) in group");
4794 for (const GroupMember &GM : G.Members) {
4795 const GroupSection *MainGroup = Map[GM.Index];
4796 if (MainGroup != &G) {
4797 W.flush();
4798 errs() << "Error: " << GM.Name << " (" << GM.Index
4799 << ") in a group " + G.Name + " (" << G.Index
4800 << ") is already in a group " + MainGroup->Name + " ("
4801 << MainGroup->Index << ")\n";
4802 errs().flush();
4803 continue;
4804 }
4805 W.startLine() << GM.Name << " (" << GM.Index << ")\n";
4806 }
4807 }
4808
4809 if (V.empty())
4810 W.startLine() << "There are no group sections in the file.\n";
4811}
4812
4813template <class ELFT> void LLVMStyle<ELFT>::printRelocations(const ELFO *Obj) {
4814 ListScope D(W, "Relocations");
4815
4816 int SectionNumber = -1;
4817 for (const Elf_Shdr &Sec : unwrapOrError(Obj->sections())) {
4818 ++SectionNumber;
4819
4820 if (Sec.sh_type != ELF::SHT_REL && Sec.sh_type != ELF::SHT_RELA &&
4821 Sec.sh_type != ELF::SHT_RELR && Sec.sh_type != ELF::SHT_ANDROID_REL &&
4822 Sec.sh_type != ELF::SHT_ANDROID_RELA &&
4823 Sec.sh_type != ELF::SHT_ANDROID_RELR)
4824 continue;
4825
4826 StringRef Name = unwrapOrError(Obj->getSectionName(&Sec));
4827
4828 W.startLine() << "Section (" << SectionNumber << ") " << Name << " {\n";
4829 W.indent();
4830
4831 printRelocations(&Sec, Obj);
4832
4833 W.unindent();
4834 W.startLine() << "}\n";
4835 }
4836}
4837
4838template <class ELFT>
4839void LLVMStyle<ELFT>::printRelocations(const Elf_Shdr *Sec, const ELFO *Obj) {
4840 const Elf_Shdr *SymTab = unwrapOrError(Obj->getSection(Sec->sh_link));
4841
4842 switch (Sec->sh_type) {
4843 case ELF::SHT_REL:
4844 for (const Elf_Rel &R : unwrapOrError(Obj->rels(Sec))) {
4845 Elf_Rela Rela;
4846 Rela.r_offset = R.r_offset;
4847 Rela.r_info = R.r_info;
4848 Rela.r_addend = 0; // FIXME: this is wrong
4849 printRelocation(Obj, Rela, SymTab, /*IsRela=*/false);
4850 }
4851 break;
4852 case ELF::SHT_RELA:
4853 for (const Elf_Rela &R : unwrapOrError(Obj->relas(Sec)))
4854 printRelocation(Obj, R, SymTab, /*IsRela=*/true);
4855 break;
4856 case ELF::SHT_RELR:
4857 case ELF::SHT_ANDROID_RELR: {
4858 Elf_Relr_Range Relrs = unwrapOrError(Obj->relrs(Sec));
4859 if (opts::RawRelr) {
4860 for (const Elf_Relr &R : Relrs)
4861 W.startLine() << W.hex(R) << "\n";
4862 } else {
4863 std::vector<Elf_Rela> RelrRelas = unwrapOrError(Obj->decode_relrs(Relrs));
4864 for (const Elf_Rela &R : RelrRelas)
4865 printRelocation(Obj, R, SymTab, /*IsRela=*/true);
4866 }
4867 break;
4868 }
4869 case ELF::SHT_ANDROID_REL:
4870 case ELF::SHT_ANDROID_RELA:
4871 for (const Elf_Rela &R : unwrapOrError(Obj->android_relas(Sec)))
4872 printRelocation(Obj, R, SymTab, /*IsRela=*/true);
4873 break;
4874 }
4875}
4876
4877template <class ELFT>
4878void LLVMStyle<ELFT>::printRelocation(const ELFO *Obj, Elf_Rela Rel,
4879 const Elf_Shdr *SymTab, bool IsRela) {
4880 SmallString<32> RelocName;
4881 Obj->getRelocationTypeName(Rel.getType(Obj->isMips64EL()), RelocName);
4882 std::string TargetName;
4883 const Elf_Sym *Sym = unwrapOrError(Obj->getRelocationSymbol(&Rel, SymTab));
4884 if (Sym && Sym->getType() == ELF::STT_SECTION) {
4885 const Elf_Shdr *Sec = unwrapOrError(
4886 Obj->getSection(Sym, SymTab, this->dumper()->getShndxTable()));
4887 TargetName = unwrapOrError(Obj->getSectionName(Sec));
4888 } else if (Sym) {
4889 StringRef StrTable = unwrapOrError(Obj->getStringTableForSymtab(*SymTab));
4890 TargetName = this->dumper()->getFullSymbolName(
4891 Sym, StrTable, SymTab->sh_type == SHT_DYNSYM /* IsDynamic */);
4892 }
4893
4894 if (opts::ExpandRelocs) {
4895 DictScope Group(W, "Relocation");
4896 W.printHex("Offset", Rel.r_offset);
4897 W.printNumber("Type", RelocName, (int)Rel.getType(Obj->isMips64EL()));
4898 W.printNumber("Symbol", !TargetName.empty() ? TargetName : "-",
4899 Rel.getSymbol(Obj->isMips64EL()));
4900 if (IsRela)
4901 W.printHex("Addend", Rel.r_addend);
4902 else
4903 W.printString("Addend",
4904 "0x" + utohexstr(Rel.r_addend) + " (real addend unknown)");
4905 } else {
4906 raw_ostream &OS = W.startLine();
4907 OS << W.hex(Rel.r_offset) << " " << RelocName << " "
4908 << (!TargetName.empty() ? TargetName : "-") << " " << W.hex(Rel.r_addend);
4909 // For RELA relocations we would need to read the bits that will be
4910 // relocated and that depends on the relocation type so is non-trivial
4911 // Print this disclaimer instead to not confuse users of llvm-readobj
4912 if (!IsRela)
4913 OS << " (real addend unknown)";
4914 OS << "\n";
4915 }
4916}
4917
4918template <class ELFT>
4919void LLVMStyle<ELFT>::printSectionHeaders(const ELFO *Obj) {
4920 ListScope SectionsD(W, "Sections");
4921
4922 int SectionIndex = -1;
4923 for (const Elf_Shdr &Sec : unwrapOrError(Obj->sections())) {
4924 ++SectionIndex;
4925
4926 StringRef Name = unwrapOrError(Obj->getSectionName(&Sec));
4927
4928 DictScope SectionD(W, "Section");
4929 W.printNumber("Index", SectionIndex);
4930 W.printNumber("Name", Name, Sec.sh_name);
4931 W.printHex(
4932 "Type",
4933 object::getELFSectionTypeName(Obj->getHeader()->e_machine, Sec.sh_type),
4934 Sec.sh_type);
4935 std::vector<EnumEntry<unsigned>> SectionFlags(std::begin(ElfSectionFlags),
4936 std::end(ElfSectionFlags));
4937 switch (Obj->getHeader()->e_machine) {
4938 case EM_ARM:
4939 SectionFlags.insert(SectionFlags.end(), std::begin(ElfARMSectionFlags),
4940 std::end(ElfARMSectionFlags));
4941 break;
4942 case EM_HEXAGON:
4943 SectionFlags.insert(SectionFlags.end(),
4944 std::begin(ElfHexagonSectionFlags),
4945 std::end(ElfHexagonSectionFlags));
4946 break;
4947 case EM_MIPS:
4948 SectionFlags.insert(SectionFlags.end(), std::begin(ElfMipsSectionFlags),
4949 std::end(ElfMipsSectionFlags));
4950 break;
4951 case EM_X86_64:
4952 SectionFlags.insert(SectionFlags.end(), std::begin(ElfX86_64SectionFlags),
4953 std::end(ElfX86_64SectionFlags));
4954 break;
4955 case EM_XCORE:
4956 SectionFlags.insert(SectionFlags.end(), std::begin(ElfXCoreSectionFlags),
4957 std::end(ElfXCoreSectionFlags));
4958 break;
4959 default:
4960 // Nothing to do.
4961 break;
4962 }
4963 W.printFlags("Flags", Sec.sh_flags, makeArrayRef(SectionFlags));
4964 W.printHex("Address", Sec.sh_addr);
4965 W.printHex("Offset", Sec.sh_offset);
4966 W.printNumber("Size", Sec.sh_size);
4967 W.printNumber("Link", Sec.sh_link);
4968 W.printNumber("Info", Sec.sh_info);
4969 W.printNumber("AddressAlignment", Sec.sh_addralign);
4970 W.printNumber("EntrySize", Sec.sh_entsize);
4971
4972 if (opts::SectionRelocations) {
4973 ListScope D(W, "Relocations");
4974 printRelocations(&Sec, Obj);
4975 }
4976
4977 if (opts::SectionSymbols) {
4978 ListScope D(W, "Symbols");
4979 const Elf_Shdr *Symtab = this->dumper()->getDotSymtabSec();
4980 StringRef StrTable = unwrapOrError(Obj->getStringTableForSymtab(*Symtab));
4981
4982 for (const Elf_Sym &Sym : unwrapOrError(Obj->symbols(Symtab))) {
4983 const Elf_Shdr *SymSec = unwrapOrError(
4984 Obj->getSection(&Sym, Symtab, this->dumper()->getShndxTable()));
4985 if (SymSec == &Sec)
4986 printSymbol(Obj, &Sym, unwrapOrError(Obj->symbols(Symtab)).begin(),
4987 StrTable, false);
4988 }
4989 }
4990
4991 if (opts::SectionData && Sec.sh_type != ELF::SHT_NOBITS) {
4992 ArrayRef<uint8_t> Data = unwrapOrError(Obj->getSectionContents(&Sec));
4993 W.printBinaryBlock(
4994 "SectionData",
4995 StringRef(reinterpret_cast<const char *>(Data.data()), Data.size()));
4996 }
4997 }
4998}
4999
5000template <class ELFT>
5001void LLVMStyle<ELFT>::printSymbol(const ELFO *Obj, const Elf_Sym *Symbol,
5002 const Elf_Sym *First, StringRef StrTable,
5003 bool IsDynamic) {
5004 unsigned SectionIndex = 0;
5005 StringRef SectionName;
5006 this->dumper()->getSectionNameIndex(Symbol, First, SectionName, SectionIndex);
5007 std::string FullSymbolName =
5008 this->dumper()->getFullSymbolName(Symbol, StrTable, IsDynamic);
5009 unsigned char SymbolType = Symbol->getType();
5010
5011 DictScope D(W, "Symbol");
5012 W.printNumber("Name", FullSymbolName, Symbol->st_name);
5013 W.printHex("Value", Symbol->st_value);
5014 W.printNumber("Size", Symbol->st_size);
5015 W.printEnum("Binding", Symbol->getBinding(), makeArrayRef(ElfSymbolBindings));
5016 if (Obj->getHeader()->e_machine == ELF::EM_AMDGPU &&
5017 SymbolType >= ELF::STT_LOOS && SymbolType < ELF::STT_HIOS)
5018 W.printEnum("Type", SymbolType, makeArrayRef(AMDGPUSymbolTypes));
5019 else
5020 W.printEnum("Type", SymbolType, makeArrayRef(ElfSymbolTypes));
5021 if (Symbol->st_other == 0)
5022 // Usually st_other flag is zero. Do not pollute the output
5023 // by flags enumeration in that case.
5024 W.printNumber("Other", 0);
5025 else {
5026 std::vector<EnumEntry<unsigned>> SymOtherFlags(std::begin(ElfSymOtherFlags),
5027 std::end(ElfSymOtherFlags));
5028 if (Obj->getHeader()->e_machine == EM_MIPS) {
5029 // Someones in their infinite wisdom decided to make STO_MIPS_MIPS16
5030 // flag overlapped with other ST_MIPS_xxx flags. So consider both
5031 // cases separately.
5032 if ((Symbol->st_other & STO_MIPS_MIPS16) == STO_MIPS_MIPS16)
5033 SymOtherFlags.insert(SymOtherFlags.end(),
5034 std::begin(ElfMips16SymOtherFlags),
5035 std::end(ElfMips16SymOtherFlags));
5036 else
5037 SymOtherFlags.insert(SymOtherFlags.end(),
5038 std::begin(ElfMipsSymOtherFlags),
5039 std::end(ElfMipsSymOtherFlags));
5040 }
5041 W.printFlags("Other", Symbol->st_other, makeArrayRef(SymOtherFlags), 0x3u);
5042 }
5043 W.printHex("Section", SectionName, SectionIndex);
5044}

5065
5066template <class ELFT> void LLVMStyle<ELFT>::printDynamic(const ELFFile<ELFT> *Obj) {
5067 Elf_Dyn_Range Table = this->dumper()->dynamic_table();
5068 if (Table.empty())
5069 return;
5070
5071 raw_ostream &OS = W.getOStream();
5072 W.startLine() << "DynamicSection [ (" << Table.size() << " entries)\n";
5073
5074 bool Is64 = ELFT::Is64Bits;
5075 if (Is64)
5076 W.startLine() << " Tag Type Name/Value\n";
5077 else
5078 W.startLine() << " Tag Type Name/Value\n";
5079 for (auto Entry : Table) {
5080 uintX_t Tag = Entry.getTag();
5081 W.startLine() << " " << format_hex(Tag, Is64 ? 18 : 10, true) << " "
5082 << format("%-21s",
5083 getTypeString(Obj->getHeader()->e_machine, Tag));
5084 this->dumper()->printDynamicEntry(OS, Tag, Entry.getVal());
5085 OS << "\n";
5086 }
5087
5088 W.startLine() << "]\n";
5089}
5090
5091template <class ELFT>
5092void LLVMStyle<ELFT>::printDynamicRelocations(const ELFO *Obj) {
5093 const DynRegionInfo &DynRelRegion = this->dumper()->getDynRelRegion();
5094 const DynRegionInfo &DynRelaRegion = this->dumper()->getDynRelaRegion();
5095 const DynRegionInfo &DynRelrRegion = this->dumper()->getDynRelrRegion();
5096 const DynRegionInfo &DynPLTRelRegion = this->dumper()->getDynPLTRelRegion();
5097 if (DynRelRegion.Size && DynRelaRegion.Size)
5098 report_fatal_error("There are both REL and RELA dynamic relocations");
5099 W.startLine() << "Dynamic Relocations {\n";
5100 W.indent();
5101 if (DynRelaRegion.Size > 0)
5102 for (const Elf_Rela &Rela : this->dumper()->dyn_relas())
5103 printDynamicRelocation(Obj, Rela);
5104 else
5105 for (const Elf_Rel &Rel : this->dumper()->dyn_rels()) {
5106 Elf_Rela Rela;
5107 Rela.r_offset = Rel.r_offset;
5108 Rela.r_info = Rel.r_info;
5109 Rela.r_addend = 0;
5110 printDynamicRelocation(Obj, Rela);
5111 }
5112 if (DynRelrRegion.Size > 0) {
5113 Elf_Relr_Range Relrs = this->dumper()->dyn_relrs();
5114 std::vector<Elf_Rela> RelrRelas = unwrapOrError(Obj->decode_relrs(Relrs));
5115 for (const Elf_Rela &Rela : RelrRelas)
5116 printDynamicRelocation(Obj, Rela);
5117 }
5118 if (DynPLTRelRegion.EntSize == sizeof(Elf_Rela))
5119 for (const Elf_Rela &Rela : DynPLTRelRegion.getAsArrayRef<Elf_Rela>())
5120 printDynamicRelocation(Obj, Rela);
5121 else
5122 for (const Elf_Rel &Rel : DynPLTRelRegion.getAsArrayRef<Elf_Rel>()) {
5123 Elf_Rela Rela;
5124 Rela.r_offset = Rel.r_offset;
5125 Rela.r_info = Rel.r_info;
5126 Rela.r_addend = 0;
5127 printDynamicRelocation(Obj, Rela);
5128 }
5129 W.unindent();
5130 W.startLine() << "}\n";
5131}
5132
5133template <class ELFT>
5134void LLVMStyle<ELFT>::printDynamicRelocation(const ELFO *Obj, Elf_Rela Rel) {
5135 SmallString<32> RelocName;
5136 Obj->getRelocationTypeName(Rel.getType(Obj->isMips64EL()), RelocName);
5137 std::string SymbolName;
5138 uint32_t SymIndex = Rel.getSymbol(Obj->isMips64EL());
5139 const Elf_Sym *Sym = this->dumper()->dynamic_symbols().begin() + SymIndex;
5140 SymbolName = maybeDemangle(
5141 unwrapOrError(Sym->getName(this->dumper()->getDynamicStringTable())));
5142 if (opts::ExpandRelocs) {
5143 DictScope Group(W, "Relocation");
5144 W.printHex("Offset", Rel.r_offset);
5145 W.printNumber("Type", RelocName, (int)Rel.getType(Obj->isMips64EL()));
5146 W.printString("Symbol", !SymbolName.empty() ? SymbolName : "-");
5147 W.printHex("Addend", Rel.r_addend);
5148 } else {
5149 raw_ostream &OS = W.startLine();
5150 OS << W.hex(Rel.r_offset) << " " << RelocName << " "
5151 << (!SymbolName.empty() ? SymbolName : "-") << " " << W.hex(Rel.r_addend)
5152 << "\n";
5153 }
5154}

5185template <class ELFT>
5186void LLVMStyle<ELFT>::printVersionSymbolSection(const ELFFile<ELFT> *Obj,
5187 const Elf_Shdr *Sec) {
5188 DictScope SS(W, "Version symbols");
5189 if (!Sec)
5190 return;
5191
5192 StringRef SecName = unwrapOrError(Obj->getSectionName(Sec));
5193 W.printNumber("Section Name", SecName, Sec->sh_name);
5194 W.printHex("Address", Sec->sh_addr);
5195 W.printHex("Offset", Sec->sh_offset);
5196 W.printNumber("Link", Sec->sh_link);
5197
5198 const uint8_t *VersymBuf =
5199 reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t *>(Obj->base() + Sec->sh_offset);
5200 const ELFDumper<ELFT> *Dumper = this->dumper();
5201 StringRef StrTable = Dumper->getDynamicStringTable();
5202
5203 // Same number of entries in the dynamic symbol table (DT_SYMTAB).
5204 ListScope Syms(W, "Symbols");
5205 for (const Elf_Sym &Sym : Dumper->dynamic_symbols()) {
5206 DictScope S(W, "Symbol");
5207 const Elf_Versym *Versym = reinterpret_cast<const Elf_Versym *>(VersymBuf);
5208 std::string FullSymbolName =
5209 Dumper->getFullSymbolName(&Sym, StrTable, true /* IsDynamic */);
5210 W.printNumber("Version", Versym->vs_index & VERSYM_VERSION);
5211 W.printString("Name", FullSymbolName);
5212 VersymBuf += sizeof(Elf_Versym);
5213 }
5214}
5215
5216template <class ELFT>
5217void LLVMStyle<ELFT>::printVersionDefinitionSection(const ELFFile<ELFT> *Obj,
5218 const Elf_Shdr *Sec) {
5219 DictScope SD(W, "SHT_GNU_verdef");
5220 if (!Sec)
5221 return;
5222
5223 const uint8_t *SecStartAddress =
5224 reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t *>(Obj->base() + Sec->sh_offset);
5225 const uint8_t *SecEndAddress = SecStartAddress + Sec->sh_size;
5226 const uint8_t *VerdefBuf = SecStartAddress;
5227 const Elf_Shdr *StrTab = unwrapOrError(Obj->getSection(Sec->sh_link));
5228
5229 unsigned VerDefsNum = Sec->sh_info;
5230 while (VerDefsNum--) {
5231 if (VerdefBuf + sizeof(Elf_Verdef) > SecEndAddress)
5232 // FIXME: report_fatal_error is not a good way to report error. We should
5233 // emit a parsing error here and below.
5234 report_fatal_error("invalid offset in the section");
5235
5236 const Elf_Verdef *Verdef = reinterpret_cast<const Elf_Verdef *>(VerdefBuf);
5237 DictScope Def(W, "Definition");
5238 W.printNumber("Version", Verdef->vd_version);
5239 W.printEnum("Flags", Verdef->vd_flags, makeArrayRef(SymVersionFlags));
5240 W.printNumber("Index", Verdef->vd_ndx);
5241 W.printNumber("Hash", Verdef->vd_hash);
5242 W.printString("Name", StringRef(reinterpret_cast<const char *>(
5243 Obj->base() + StrTab->sh_offset +
5244 Verdef->getAux()->vda_name)));
5245 if (!Verdef->vd_cnt)
5246 report_fatal_error("at least one definition string must exist");
5247 if (Verdef->vd_cnt > 2)
5248 report_fatal_error("more than one predecessor is not expected");
5249
5250 if (Verdef->vd_cnt == 2) {
5251 const uint8_t *VerdauxBuf =
5252 VerdefBuf + Verdef->vd_aux + Verdef->getAux()->vda_next;
5253 const Elf_Verdaux *Verdaux =
5254 reinterpret_cast<const Elf_Verdaux *>(VerdauxBuf);
5255 W.printString("Predecessor",
5256 StringRef(reinterpret_cast<const char *>(
5257 Obj->base() + StrTab->sh_offset + Verdaux->vda_name)));
5258 }
5259 VerdefBuf += Verdef->vd_next;
5260 }
5261}

5263template <class ELFT>
5264void LLVMStyle<ELFT>::printVersionDependencySection(const ELFFile<ELFT> *Obj,
5265 const Elf_Shdr *Sec) {
5266 DictScope SD(W, "SHT_GNU_verneed");
5267 if (!Sec)
5268 return;
5269
5270 const uint8_t *SecData =
5271 reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t *>(Obj->base() + Sec->sh_offset);
5272 const Elf_Shdr *StrTab = unwrapOrError(Obj->getSection(Sec->sh_link));
5273
5274 const uint8_t *VerneedBuf = SecData;
5275 unsigned VerneedNum = Sec->sh_info;
5276 for (unsigned I = 0; I < VerneedNum; ++I) {
5277 const Elf_Verneed *Verneed =
5278 reinterpret_cast<const Elf_Verneed *>(VerneedBuf);
5279 DictScope Entry(W, "Dependency");
5280 W.printNumber("Version", Verneed->vn_version);
5281 W.printNumber("Count", Verneed->vn_cnt);
5282 W.printString("FileName",
5283 StringRef(reinterpret_cast<const char *>(
5284 Obj->base() + StrTab->sh_offset + Verneed->vn_file)));
5285
5286 const uint8_t *VernauxBuf = VerneedBuf + Verneed->vn_aux;
5287 ListScope L(W, "Entries");
5288 for (unsigned J = 0; J < Verneed->vn_cnt; ++J) {
5289 const Elf_Vernaux *Vernaux =
5290 reinterpret_cast<const Elf_Vernaux *>(VernauxBuf);
5291 DictScope Entry(W, "Entry");
5292 W.printNumber("Hash", Vernaux->vna_hash);
5293 W.printEnum("Flags", Vernaux->vna_flags, makeArrayRef(SymVersionFlags));
5294 W.printNumber("Index", Vernaux->vna_other);
5295 W.printString("Name",
5296 StringRef(reinterpret_cast<const char *>(
5297 Obj->base() + StrTab->sh_offset + Vernaux->vna_name)));
5298 VernauxBuf += Vernaux->vna_next;
5299 }
5300 VerneedBuf += Verneed->vn_next;
5301 }
5302}

5309template <class ELFT>
5310void LLVMStyle<ELFT>::printCGProfile(const ELFFile<ELFT> *Obj) {
5311 ListScope L(W, "CGProfile");
5312 if (!this->dumper()->getDotCGProfileSec())
5313 return;

5315 unwrapOrError(Obj->template getSectionContentsAsArray<Elf_CGProfile>(
5316 this->dumper()->getDotCGProfileSec()));

5318 DictScope D(W, "CGProfileEntry");
5319 W.printNumber("From", this->dumper()->getStaticSymbolName(CGPE.cgp_from),
5320 CGPE.cgp_from);

5327template <class ELFT>
5328void LLVMStyle<ELFT>::printAddrsig(const ELFFile<ELFT> *Obj) {
5329 ListScope L(W, "Addrsig");
5330 if (!this->dumper()->getDotAddrsigSec())
5331 return;
5332 ArrayRef<uint8_t> Contents = unwrapOrError(
5333 Obj->getSectionContents(this->dumper()->getDotAddrsigSec()));
5334 const uint8_t *Cur = Contents.begin();
5335 const uint8_t *End = Contents.end();
5336 while (Cur != End) {
5337 unsigned Size;
5338 const char *Err;
5339 uint64_t SymIndex = decodeULEB128(Cur, &Size, End, &Err);
5340 if (Err)
5341 reportError(Err);
5342 W.printNumber("Sym", this->dumper()->getStaticSymbolName(SymIndex),
5343 SymIndex);
5344 Cur += Size;
5345 }
5346}
5347
5348template <typename ELFT>
5349static void printGNUNoteLLVMStyle(uint32_t NoteType, ArrayRef<uint8_t> Desc,
5350 ScopedPrinter &W) {
5351 switch (NoteType) {
5352 default:
5353 return;
5354 case ELF::NT_GNU_ABI_TAG: {
5355 const GNUAbiTag &AbiTag = getGNUAbiTag<ELFT>(Desc);
5356 if (!AbiTag.IsValid) {
5357 W.printString("ABI", "<corrupt GNU_ABI_TAG>");
5358 } else {
5359 W.printString("OS", AbiTag.OSName);
5360 W.printString("ABI", AbiTag.ABI);
5361 }
5362 break;
5363 }
5364 case ELF::NT_GNU_BUILD_ID: {
5365 W.printString("Build ID", getGNUBuildId(Desc));
5366 break;
5367 }
5368 case ELF::NT_GNU_GOLD_VERSION:
5369 W.printString("Version", getGNUGoldVersion(Desc));
5370 break;
5371 case ELF::NT_GNU_PROPERTY_TYPE_0:
5372 ListScope D(W, "Property");
5373 for (const auto &Property : getGNUPropertyList<ELFT>(Desc))
5374 W.printString(Property);
5375 break;
5376 }
5377}

5379template <class ELFT>
5380void LLVMStyle<ELFT>::printNotes(const ELFFile<ELFT> *Obj) {
5381 ListScope L(W, "Notes");
5382
5383 auto PrintHeader = [&](const typename ELFT::Off Offset,
5384 const typename ELFT::Addr Size) {
5385 W.printHex("Offset", Offset);
5386 W.printHex("Size", Size);
5387 };
5388
5389 auto ProcessNote = [&](const Elf_Note &Note) {
5390 DictScope D2(W, "Note");
5391 StringRef Name = Note.getName();
5392 ArrayRef<uint8_t> Descriptor = Note.getDesc();
5393 Elf_Word Type = Note.getType();
5394
5395 W.printString("Owner", Name);
5396 W.printHex("Data size", Descriptor.size());
5397 if (Name == "GNU") {
5398 W.printString("Type", getGNUNoteTypeName(Type));
5399 printGNUNoteLLVMStyle<ELFT>(Type, Descriptor, W);
5400 } else if (Name == "FreeBSD") {
5401 W.printString("Type", getFreeBSDNoteTypeName(Type));
5402 } else if (Name == "AMD") {
5403 W.printString("Type", getAMDNoteTypeName(Type));
5404 const AMDNote N = getAMDNote<ELFT>(Type, Descriptor);
5405 if (!N.Type.empty())
5406 W.printString(N.Type, N.Value);
5407 } else if (Name == "AMDGPU") {
5408 W.printString("Type", getAMDGPUNoteTypeName(Type));
5409 const AMDGPUNote N = getAMDGPUNote<ELFT>(Type, Descriptor);
5410 if (!N.Type.empty())
5411 W.printString(N.Type, N.Value);
5412 } else {
5413 StringRef NoteType = getGenericNoteTypeName(Type);
5414 if (!NoteType.empty())
5415 W.printString("Type", NoteType);
5416 else
5417 W.printString("Type",
5418 "Unknown (" + to_string(format_hex(Type, 10)) + ")");
5419 }
5420 };
5421
5422 if (Obj->getHeader()->e_type == ELF::ET_CORE) {
5423 for (const auto &P : unwrapOrError(Obj->program_headers())) {
5424 if (P.p_type != PT_NOTE)
5425 continue;
5426 DictScope D(W, "NoteSection");
5427 PrintHeader(P.p_offset, P.p_filesz);
5428 Error Err = Error::success();
5429 for (const auto &Note : Obj->notes(P, Err))
5430 ProcessNote(Note);
5431 if (Err)
5432 error(std::move(Err));
5433 }
5434 } else {
5435 for (const auto &S : unwrapOrError(Obj->sections())) {
5436 if (S.sh_type != SHT_NOTE)
5437 continue;
5438 DictScope D(W, "NoteSection");
5439 PrintHeader(S.sh_offset, S.sh_size);
5440 Error Err = Error::success();
5441 for (const auto &Note : Obj->notes(S, Err))
5442 ProcessNote(Note);
5443 if (Err)
5444 error(std::move(Err));
5445 }
5446 }
5447}
5448
5449template <class ELFT>
5450void LLVMStyle<ELFT>::printELFLinkerOptions(const ELFFile<ELFT> *Obj) {
5451 ListScope L(W, "LinkerOptions");
5452
5453 for (const Elf_Shdr &Shdr : unwrapOrError(Obj->sections())) {
5454 if (Shdr.sh_type != ELF::SHT_LLVM_LINKER_OPTIONS)
5455 continue;
5456
5457 ArrayRef<uint8_t> Contents = unwrapOrError(Obj->getSectionContents(&Shdr));
5458 for (const uint8_t *P = Contents.begin(), *E = Contents.end(); P < E; ) {
5459 StringRef Key = StringRef(reinterpret_cast<const char *>(P));
5460 StringRef Value =
5461 StringRef(reinterpret_cast<const char *>(P) + Key.size() + 1);
5462
5463 W.printString(Key, Value);
5464
5465 P = P + Key.size() + Value.size() + 2;
5466 }
5467 }
5468}
5469
5470template <class ELFT>
5471void LLVMStyle<ELFT>::printMipsGOT(const MipsGOTParser<ELFT> &Parser) {
5472 auto PrintEntry = [&](const Elf_Addr *E) {
5473 W.printHex("Address", Parser.getGotAddress(E));
5474 W.printNumber("Access", Parser.getGotOffset(E));
5475 W.printHex("Initial", *E);
5476 };
5477
5478 DictScope GS(W, Parser.IsStatic ? "Static GOT" : "Primary GOT");
5479
5480 W.printHex("Canonical gp value", Parser.getGp());
5481 {
5482 ListScope RS(W, "Reserved entries");
5483 {
5484 DictScope D(W, "Entry");
5485 PrintEntry(Parser.getGotLazyResolver());
5486 W.printString("Purpose", StringRef("Lazy resolver"));
5487 }
5488
5489 if (Parser.getGotModulePointer()) {
5490 DictScope D(W, "Entry");
5491 PrintEntry(Parser.getGotModulePointer());
5492 W.printString("Purpose", StringRef("Module pointer (GNU extension)"));
5493 }
5494 }
5495 {
5496 ListScope LS(W, "Local entries");
5497 for (auto &E : Parser.getLocalEntries()) {
5498 DictScope D(W, "Entry");
5499 PrintEntry(&E);
5500 }
5501 }
5502
5503 if (Parser.IsStatic)
5504 return;
5505
5506 {
5507 ListScope GS(W, "Global entries");
5508 for (auto &E : Parser.getGlobalEntries()) {
5509 DictScope D(W, "Entry");
5510
5511 PrintEntry(&E);
5512
5513 const Elf_Sym *Sym = Parser.getGotSym(&E);
5514 W.printHex("Value", Sym->st_value);
5515 W.printEnum("Type", Sym->getType(), makeArrayRef(ElfSymbolTypes));
5516
5517 unsigned SectionIndex = 0;
5518 StringRef SectionName;
5519 this->dumper()->getSectionNameIndex(
5520 Sym, this->dumper()->dynamic_symbols().begin(), SectionName,
5521 SectionIndex);
5522 W.printHex("Section", SectionName, SectionIndex);
5523
5524 std::string SymName = this->dumper()->getFullSymbolName(
5525 Sym, this->dumper()->getDynamicStringTable(), true);
5526 W.printNumber("Name", SymName, Sym->st_name);
5527 }
5528 }
5529
5530 W.printNumber("Number of TLS and multi-GOT entries",
5531 uint64_t(Parser.getOtherEntries().size()));
5532}
5533
5534template <class ELFT>
5535void LLVMStyle<ELFT>::printMipsPLT(const MipsGOTParser<ELFT> &Parser) {
5536 auto PrintEntry = [&](const Elf_Addr *E) {
5537 W.printHex("Address", Parser.getPltAddress(E));
5538 W.printHex("Initial", *E);
5539 };
5540
5541 DictScope GS(W, "PLT GOT");
5542
5543 {
5544 ListScope RS(W, "Reserved entries");
5545 {
5546 DictScope D(W, "Entry");
5547 PrintEntry(Parser.getPltLazyResolver());
5548 W.printString("Purpose", StringRef("PLT lazy resolver"));
5549 }
5550
5551 if (auto E = Parser.getPltModulePointer()) {
5552 DictScope D(W, "Entry");
5553 PrintEntry(E);
5554 W.printString("Purpose", StringRef("Module pointer"));
5555 }
5556 }
5557 {
5558 ListScope LS(W, "Entries");
5559 for (auto &E : Parser.getPltEntries()) {
5560 DictScope D(W, "Entry");
5561 PrintEntry(&E);
5562
5563 const Elf_Sym *Sym = Parser.getPltSym(&E);
5564 W.printHex("Value", Sym->st_value);
5565 W.printEnum("Type", Sym->getType(), makeArrayRef(ElfSymbolTypes));
5566
5567 unsigned SectionIndex = 0;
5568 StringRef SectionName;
5569 this->dumper()->getSectionNameIndex(
5570 Sym, this->dumper()->dynamic_symbols().begin(), SectionName,
5571 SectionIndex);
5572 W.printHex("Section", SectionName, SectionIndex);
5573
5574 std::string SymName =
5575 this->dumper()->getFullSymbolName(Sym, Parser.getPltStrTable(), true);
5576 W.printNumber("Name", SymName, Sym->st_name);
5577 }
5578 }
